#1.CAMP SITE  *****************************
line101 = "You enter a small clearing in the Pinerift Forest. There is a camp site with  extra tinder sitting next to a carefully dug firepit surrounded by stones. Looks like a safe spot to REST up before continuing on your journey.\n" 
line102 = "You enter a small clearing in the Pinerift Forest. There is a camp site with a carefully dug firepit surrounded by stones. The extra tinder has been all used up. Looks like a safe spot to REST up before continuing on your journey.\n" 
  #EXPLORE
line103 = "You look around and see there is a downward sloped path to your NORTH heading deeper into the forest, a small and worn dirt footpath to the WEST, and an old yet sturdy cobbled road to the SOUTH leading into the Royal Capital.\n\nThe campsite seems to be regularly used by other travelers. A well constructed fire pit sits at the center with a carefully placed pile of tinder sitting next to a carved log bench. It looks comfortable enough to take a brief REST.\n"  
line104 = "You look around and see there is a downward sloped path to your NORTH heading deeper into the forest, a small and worn dirt footpath to the WEST, and an old yet sturdy cobbled road to the SOUTH leading into the Royal Capital.\n\nThe campsite seems to be regularly used by other travelers. A well constructed fire pit sits at the center next to a carved log bench. The pile of tinder that was here has been all used up. It looks like a comfortable place to take a break.\n"  

line105 = "You take a moment to rest by the camp fire. The warmth of the fire is a relaxing comfort. As you sit by the fire you feel your strength returning.\n"

#2.Royal Capital  *********************************
line201 = "You stand at the center of the Royal Capital and breathe in the smells of the market and nearby fountain.\n" 
  #EXPLORE
line202 = "From the town center there is a shop for Adventurers to the EAST, the Royal Castle to the SOUTH, and an inn advertising beds available to the WEST.\n\nAt the very center of the Capital is a large marble fountain with carvings of various sea-beasts and serpents and a statue of a warrior mermaid holding a long trident and small strapped shield.\n\nAt first glance the Royal Capital is a vibrant and beautiful community, but there is a dark air that hangs over the townsfolk. You sense the cause of this anxiety stems from the wicked Tower looming across the forest...\n" 
 #town part 2
line203 = "You make your way through the crowded streets before stopping on the corner of a busy intersection.\n"
line204 = "Buildings and homes line the narrow streets, bustling with activity. The city is alive with the sounds of townsfolk going about their daily lives. You can spot the Inn WEST of where you are standing, and a church to the NORTH.\n"

#church
line205 = "You step into the large church and are greeted by the soft light filtering through the stained glass windows. The scent of incense fills the air as you take a moment to reflect on your journey.\n"
line206 = "The church is a peaceful sanctuary amidst the bustling city. Rows of mmostly empty wooden pews face a grand altar adorned with intricate carvings and religious symbols. The soft glow of candles illuminates the space, casting flickering shadows on the walls. A sense of calm washes over you as you take in the serene atmosphere.\n"
#3.Shop********************************
line301 = 'The shop keep greets you and welcomes you to browse his wares.\n"Please let me know if you would like to BUY or SELL anything.\n' 
    #Harbor market
line302 = 'You step into a bustling market along the piers. You stop at a trading cart with a crooked sign reading; "Everything an Adventurer needs here!".' 
  #EXPLORE
    #Harbor market
line303 = "Ships and their cargo can be seen being unloaded at the docks. Trading stands and carts fill the streets here; traders from all over have come to the Harbor Town to peddle their wares. Everything from fresh fish to fine jewelry can be found sold here. The Adventurer's cart looks like it will have some useful items to BUY..."
    #city shop
line304 = "Looking around the shop you see cluttered shelves filled with various strange bits of monsters, small vials filled with every color and viscosity of liquid, and carefully placed SMOKE BOMBS in a glass case. The shop keep smiles and urges you to BUY anything that catches your eye.\n" 
    #traveling merchant
line305 =  'Out of the blue you can hear the sound of cart wheels rapidly approaching you. Before you know it a lanky gnome pulling a cart filled with supplies runs up next to you.\n\n"OH OH OH! A customer! Yes yes yes! Come check my wares! Buy buy buy!\n"'

    #City shop - Speech
line306 = '"Welcome to my shop, Adventurer! I have many fine items for sale that will surely help you on your quest. Take a look around and let me know if you need any assistance."\n'
line306b = '"Say, have you heard anything from the village EAST of here? I often buy goods from the farmer that lives there but it\'s been a while since I\'ve seen him. I hope he is well.."\n'
line306c = '"Thanks for stopping by again. Tell the Farmer I said hello next time you see him."\n'    

   # Harbor Market - Speech
line307 = 'You try getting the attention of one of the traders, but it seems they are too busy to notice you. If you aren\'t interested in buying or selling, they aren\'t interested in talking.\n'
#4.Inn*************************************
line401 = "The Inn keep motions you to the counter and offers you a bed.\nTaking a REST in a proper bed will surely rejuvenate you before your next battle.\n(REST at the Inn for 40GP)\n" 
line401b = "The tavern owner rushes over to greet you. He eagerly offers you an available bed.\nTaking a REST in a proper bed will surely rejuvenate you before your next battle.\n(REST at the tavern for 40GP)\n" 
line401c = 'You walk through the door of the Harbor Inn and are immediately greeted by the proprietor before she offers you a room.\nTaking a REST in a proper bed will surely rejuvenate you before your next battle.\n(REST at the Inn for 40GP)\n'
line401d = 'You enter the Dwarf Village Inn and are greeted by a stout dwarf behind the counter. He offers you a bed for the night.\nTaking a REST in a proper bed will surely rejuvenate you before your next battle.\n(REST at the Inn for 40GP)\n'
  
  #EXPLORE
line404 = 'Behind the counter is a plump, jolly older man finding things to clean. There are a number of patrons sitting around tables on the main floor discussing business and travel over drinks. you spot an orange cat sleeping on a cushion with the name "MILO" embroidered on it. Near the entrance is a set of stairs leading to the inn beds on the second floor. \n' 
line404b = "The tavern is a quaint building with a single room for guests. Travelers must not be too common around here. The tavern owner's wife can be heard tending to the kitchen, prepping for dinner at the restaurant they run inside. A pair of ceramic pet bowls labeled 'Yuffie' and 'Iggy' sit behind the front counter.\n"
line404c = 'The main room of the Harbor Inn is filled with travelers from all over making conversation and exchanging news. It would appear that only a few vacancies remain. Maybe getting a warm bed and a hot meal would be a wise idea. As you stand there and ponder your next actions a cat rubs up against your legs. The bell on his collar is engraved with the name "Ardyn".'
line404d = 'The Dwarf Village Inn is a cozy establishment filled with the smell of hearty cooking and the sound of jovial dwarven laughter. The innkeeper, a stout dwarf with a bushy beard, is busy polishing mugs behind the counter. A few patrons sit at wooden tables, sharing stories of their travels. A small fire crackles in the hearth, casting a warm glow throughout the room.\n'

 #speech 1
line405 = '"We used to get a lot more travelers coming from Harbor Town to the NORTH, but with Smeldar\'s Tower appearing again people are too afraid to make the journey. I hope things get better soon...\n"'
line405b = '"This village has always been a quiet place, but these days it feels even more isolated. I\'ve heard rumors Smeldar has returned to seek vengeance on the kingdom. It can\'t possibly be true, can it?"\n'
line405c = '"The Harbor Town used to be a bustling trade hub, with people coming from kingdoms far and wide but with Smeldar\'s Tower looming over, many traders have ceased their journeys here. I pray for safer days ahead...\n"'
line405d = '"Nut too many tavelr\'s coom to the village, especially o\' yer size. Ah\'ve got a bed for ye if ye need, but it mey be a tite squeeze..."\n'
 #speech 2
line406 = '"Taking a REST at a campfire is a good way to recoup some strength while on your journey, but nothing beats a good rest in a proper bed. A night at the inn is well worth the cost to fully recover."\n'
line406b = '"Have you heard about ROYAL JELLY? Giant Bees make it and store it in their hives. Adventurers from generations past would line their potion bottles with it to improve their efficacy. There\'s a hive nearby if I\'m not mistaken..."\n'
line406c = '"The captain at the docks has been looking for someone to hire for something. Maybe an adventurer like yourself could help?"\n'
line406d = """"'Av ye hurd th' 'ol tales aboot th' Drake Mountains? Legends sey the 'ol Dragon lord still livs up on th' peak. Thos who dare spek 'is name in th' 'ol tung on the top 'o th' mountain mey wak 'im frum 'is slumbr"\n"""

#5.CASTLE*******************************
line501 = "You step into the great hall of the Royal Castle. The Princess Serlida is seated on her throne awaiting those who seek audience with her ladyship. (Type SPEAK to interact.)\n"
  #EXPLORE
line502 = "The well weathered outer walls betray the pristine and elegant interior. Red and gold tapestries line the walls, some depicting heroic deeds from ages past. Stained glass windows near the ceiling bring in a flood of multicolored light that fills the room. A massive tapestry depicting the royal coat of arms hangs above the Princess Serlida and her throne. Guards wielding halberds flank either side of the Princess Serlida and servants can be seen scurrying all around carrying out their daily tasks. Everyone has an anxious look on their faces.\n" 
  #SPEAK
line505 = "You approach the royal advisor and request an audience with the Princess Serlida. Audience is granted.\n" 
line506 = '"Noble Adventurer, hear my plea; our kingdom has been plagued by the evil warlock Smeldar since it was founded many generations ago. His tower is a harbinger of dark times and appears whenever Smeldar begins assembling his wicked army. Please venture NORTH through the Pinerift Forest to the wretched tower and put a stop to Smeldar before his power returns and he regains his full strength"\n' 
line507 = '"They say that Smeldar\'s Tower is locked by powerful magic. Only the enchanted dragon bone keys held by his most loyal minions can unlock its doors. Please locate these keys and put an end to Smeldar\'s tyranny."\n' 
line508 = '"We have heard reports of Goblins nesting in the caves EAST of the Pinerift Forest. They have likely joined forces with Smeldar once again...Be on your guard."\n' 
line508b = '"Word has spread you defeated the Goblin Queen and helped reduce the goblin threat! And you have located a dragon bone key? We are grateful for your service, hero. I pray for your safety as you continue your quest."\n'
line509 = '"The swamps in the NORTH WEST are said to be home to dangerous creatures, many loyal to Smeldar. Proceed with caution."\n'
line509b = '"Your success in the swamps has brought hope to our people. With each victory against Smeldar\'s forces, we grow stronger. May fortune continue to favor you."\n'
line510 = '"An encampment of Orcs has been spotted NORTH EAST of the kingdom, on its borders. We must prepare for Smeldar\'s invasion. Please, stop them before it is too late."\n'
line510b = '"Your victory against the Orcs has bought us precious time to prepare our defenses. The people of the kingdom are grateful for your bravery. May your journey continue to be blessed."\n'
line511 = '"Old fables tell of a castle hidden deep in the forests to the EAST. Once it belonged to a fairy king and queen, but Smeldar\'s forces overthrew them and the castle was granted to his general, the Vampire Lord. They say the forest and castle have been cursed ever since. How true could those old legends be?"\n'
line511b = '"Unbelievable that the old legends were true all along! It\'s hard to imagine such darkness and wickedness. Your victories have given my people hope in these dark times. We are forever in your debt."\n'
line512 = '"If you have all four dragon bone keys, you should be able to enter Smeldar\'s Tower... The Warlock is sure to have traps and powerful defenses awaiting you. Please make sure you are well prepared."\n'
#6.CLIFF*************************
line601 = "The woods begin to thin as you approach another clearing. You stand near a cliff over-looking the vast Pinerift Forest and surrounding lands.\n" 
  #EXPLORE
line602 = "Taking a look over the cliff you can see the lands below. To the NORTH looming over the surrounding area is the dark, gnarled spire known as the Tower of Smeldar. Looking WEST you can make out a river flowing NORTH feeding into a sizable lake. You can make out a faint glow EAST in the Pinerift Forest, just past a rocky hill. Unless you can fly there doesn't look to be any safe way down the cliff.\nAt the base of an olive tree near the edge of the cliff you notice something shining in the sun. (Type EXAMINE to inspect.)\n"
line603 = "Taking a look over the cliff you can see the lands below. To the NORTH looming over the surrounding area is the dark, gnarled spire known as the Tower of Smeldar. Looking WEST you can make out the Serpents River flowing NORTH into Echobo Lake. You can make out a faint glow EAST in the Pinerift Forest, just past a rocky hill. Unless you can fly there doesn't look to be any safe way down the cliff.\n"
  #EXAMINE
line604 = "Near the base of the olive tree's trunk is a round, shining object embedded in a burl. The tree must have grown around whatever it is. If you had something to cut the wood you may be able to retrieve it...\n" 
line605 = "Near the base of the olive tree's trunk is a round, shining object embedded in a burl. You could probably CUT it away or just LEAVE it alone." 
line605b = "You take your AXE and carefully start chopping the burl off. After some time you manage to free the item and discover it is an old PENDANT. You place it in your bag." #72
line605c = "You decide not to disturb the object.\n" 
line605d = 'The PENDANT has been freed from the olive tree.\n'

line609 = "You look to the WEST down the edge of the cliff. Unless you're a bird, good luck getting down from here.\n" 
line610 = "You look down the edge of the cliff and decide to jump off. Not the brightest thing to do was it?\n" 

line611 = "Miraculously, you survive the fall. You can't tell if those branches you fell through broke your fall or your ribs. Maybe don't do that again?\n" 

#7.FOREST*************************************
line701 = "You come to a crossroads deep in the Pinerift Forest. It's so dark it almost appears to be night. You stand there and ponder your next steps.\n" 
  #EXPLORE
line702 = 'The air is unusually stale for a forest... you sense something sinister lurking deeper in the woods. There is a crooked sign off the road that reads "← LAKE. ↓ CAPITAL. SHRINE →". You also notice a path to the NORTH that has long been overgrown. A great deal of strange sounds are emanating from the woods, and in the distance you can hear howling...\n' 
line703 = 'The air is unusually stale for a forest... you sense something sinister lurking deeper in the woods. There is a crooked sign off the road that reads "← LAKE. ↓ CAPITAL. SHRINE →". You also notice a path to the NORTH that has long been overgrown. The forest is eerily quiet now; you make sure to be on your guard...\n'
  # Forest - EAST
line704 = "The eastern forest path is dark and gloomy. You stop and take a moment to get your bearings on the cramped trail.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line705 = "The thinning path twists from EAST to WEST through the Pinerift Forest. Just off the path the woods are filled with knobby roots and an impenetrable wall of branches and pine needles that impede travel. There is a chill in the air; you can hear the rustling and snapping of twigs beyond the trees... you get the sense something is lurking nearby.\n"
line706 = "The thinning path twists from EAST to WEST through the Pinerift Forest. Just off the path the woods are filled with knobby roots and an impenetrable wall of branches and pine needles that impede travel. You no longer sense anything stalking you; regardless you remain vigilant while traveling through the forest.\n"
  #ambush
line707 = "While walking through the forest you begin to hear the rustling of branches and crunching of leaves on the ground. The sounds begin to draw closer and closer as you continue down the path. Suddenly you hear a growl come from behind and when you swing around to look you find a Dire Wolf standing before you! The massive wolf leaps towards you and snaps its powerful jaw just shy of your leg! You draw your weapon and prepare for combat."
line708 = "With the Dire Wolf defeated, you look across the battlefield and see a broken WOLF FANG lying on the ground before you. You pick up the Dire Wolf's broken fang and take it as a trophy."
  #Forest - WEST
line709 = "The western forest path begins to widen and the sun's rays begin to break through to the forest floor. You take a moment to soak in the sun before continuing on your journey.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line710 = "The sun is bright and warm in this part of the woods; a sharp contrast to the cold, dark woods to the EAST. Standing on the path here it is easy to forget that the forest has been tainted by Smeldar's evil. The sound of flowing water can be heard coming from the WEST."

#8.HILL*****************************
line801 = "You come to a large stone hill jutting diagonally into the sky. You stand on the path several yards outside a cave tucked into the side of the hill.\n" 
  #EXPLORE
line802 = 'Small animal bones litter the entrance to the cave EAST of you. Large claw marks can be seen across several nearby trees. Past the HILL and in the woods to the NORTH you can just make out a blue glow through the trees. The path continues in the direction of the glow. Looking SOUTH you can see a partially felled tree. Type "EXAMINE" to inspect.\n' 
line804 = 'Small animal bones litter the entrance to the cave EAST of you. Large claw marks can be seen across several nearby trees. Past the HILL and in the woods to the NORTH you can just make out a blue glow through the trees. The path continues in the direction of the glow. Looking SOUTH a path has been cleared. The woods sound like they are teeming with life in that direction and you catch a sweet smell in the air.\n' 
  #EXAMINE
line805 = "The tree appears to have been struck by lightning and broke; it's tipped over and is blocking the path SOUTH. If only you had a way to finish knocking the tree over...\n" 
line805b = "The tree appears to have been struck by lightning and broken; it's tipped over and is blocking the path SOUTH. You'll need to finish knocking it down to get through. Your AXE should do the job. CUT the tree down, or LEAVE it be?\n"
line806 = "You take your AXE and begin chopping into the tree. After a few good whacks the tree finishes toppling over. A family of squirrels curses you for destroying their home. Don't worry though; squirrel magic is lame. You can easily step over the trunk and continue now.\n" 
line806b = "You decide to leave the tree alone.\n"
line811 = "The tree has been cleared from the path. You can head SOUTH now.\n"
line812 = "The way SOUTH is blocked by a damaged tree. If only you had a way to finish knocking the tree over...\n"
#9.Cave**************************************
line901 = "As you enter the cave a foul stench fills your nostrils. You soon discover the source; a sleeping Bear lies in front of you.\n" 
line902 = "As you enter the cave a foul stench fills your nostrils. The Bear is gone but its smell lingers.\n" 
  #Examine
line903 = "You notice the Bear is guarding a large woodcutting AXE. There's no way you're getting it without dealing with that Bear. Do you POKE or BACK out?\n" 
line904 = "You notice the Bear is guarding a large woodcutting AXE. There's no way you're getting it without dealing with that Bear. You remember the SALMON you found at the WATERFALL. Maybe this will help? Do you POKE, FEED, or BACK out?\n" 
  #EXPLORE
line906 = "The cave reeks of something foul, like rotting fish. It's dark, but it appears that the cave continues on EAST. Just a few paces ahead, a sleeping Bear lies; it seems to be guarding something. EXAMINE for a closer look?\n" 
line906b = "The cave reeks of something foul, like rotting fish. Now that the Bear is gone the stench isn't quite so bad... It's dark, but it appears that the cave continues on EAST.\n"
line907 = "You decide messing with a sleeping Bear isn't a wise idea and back away.\n"
  #EAST
line909 = "It is much too dark to go any deeper into the cave. You'll need a light source to make it through.\n"
  #Bear Combat/Defeat
line911 = "You creep up on the Bear and get as close as you can before using a nearby stick to poke the Bear right in the eye. That was a wise idea. The Bear's roar echoes in the cave as they shuffle around, still only half coherent. The Bear quickly wakes up and realizes you are the cause of their discomfort. Good luck with that.\n" 
line912 = "The Bear is vanquished and the AXE is now free for the taking. You grab the AXE and celebrate your victory.\n" 
line912b = "What was a Bear doing with an AXE in the first place?..\n" 
line913 = "You grab the SALMON from your pack and toss it in front of the Bear. The Bear's nose twitches and slowly turns towards the SALMON. The Bear wakes up and sleepily looks over at you before scooping up the SALMON and exiting the cave. You grab the AXE as soon as the Bear leaves.\n" 
# Dungeon Cave 1
line914 = "The Bear is still sleeping. You should probably deal with it before moving deeper...\n"
line915 = "You turn on your lantern. Now you should have no trouble seeing through the cave\n" 
line915b = "You cast an illuminating spell. Now you should have no trouble seeing through the cave\n" 
line916 = "Taking care on the uneven cave floor, you come to a fork in the path.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line917 = "From the intersection, the cave seems to continue either NORTH or SOUTH. The path returning to the entrance in the WEST is particularly narrow. Too narrow for a Bear to get through. You look around and see large bones littering the ground. Some are animals, but the majority are distinctly human.\n"
#Dungeon Cave 2
line922 = "The cave opens up slightly and you enter a musty room filled with boxes, barrels, and sacks.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line923 = "The stockpile of items is an unexpected find deep in the cave. Most appear to have been ruined by the constant dripping from the stalactites above. Nearly everything is moldy here. You see a chest in the center of the room that seems to have been untouched by mold yet. You can EXAMINE the chest for a closer look.\n"
line924 = "The chest is empty and the Hobgoblin slain. It would seem that this is where these Goblins store their stolen spoils from the travelers they ambush along the roads.\n"
  #EXAMINE
line925 = "You walk up to the chest at the center of the room and take notice that there is no lock. It looks like it was recently brought here since it's the only thing not covered in mildew. It might still have something valuable inside. OPEN, SMASH, or BACK out?\n" 
line926 = "You open the chest and immediately are assaulted by a Hobgoblin from within! You just barely manage to evade their wild charge as they come at you. You quickly prepare yourself for combat!\n"
line927 = "You finish off the Hobgoblin and catch your breath. You notice they dropped an IRON KEY when they leaped from the chest. You pick it up and take it as a consolation. Maybe it will come in handy later.\n"
line928 = "You decide that it's better to leave the chest alone for now. These things usually end up being traps for novice Adventurers anyway.\n"
line928b = "You look inside the chest. Thankfully no more Hobgoblins pop out, but it's completely empty.\n"
line929 = "You grab a nearby maul and smash open the chest. A terrible yelp came from within the chest and suddenly a Hobgoblin leapt forth! You just barely manage to evade their wild charge as they come at you. You quickly prepare yourself for combat!\n"

#DUNGEOUN Cave 3
line931 = "You enter a narrow passage flanked by craggily walls on the EAST and WEST.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line932a = "The passage here is a narrow tunnel descending SOUTH, deeper underground. The walls on either side are a rough limestone worn from many years of erosion; they feel slightly damp.\n"

#DUNGEON Cave 4
line935 = "You step out of the tunnel and enter an open room within the cave. As you step into the room you can hear a snarling and wild laughter coming from a large pit ahead. Before you can react a Goblin Gang begins crawling from the pit and surrounds you!\n"
line936 = "You defeat the last of the Goblin Gang and revel in your victory. You take one of the fallen Goblin's GOBLIN CHOPPER as a reward for your victory. You try to convince yourself it's not your fault there are so many Goblin widows and orphans.\n"
line937 = "You reach an open area with a large pit to the SOUTH/WEST. You take caution against another ambush.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line938 = "The underground of the cave has opened up into a wide cavern. The current path has two ways, back NORTH up the tunnel to the entrance, and EAST to the heart of the cave. To the SOUTH and WEST a massive pit leads down to a seemingly endless void. This is likely the nest of the Goblin Den.\nAt the end of the path to the EAST is an iron door blocking the way forward. EXAMINE the door and see if there's a way through?\n"
line939 = "The underground of the cave has opened up into a wide cavern. The current path has two ways, back NORTH up the tunnel to the entrance, and forward to the EAST to the heart of the cave. To the SOUTH and WEST a massive pit leads down to a seemingly endless void. This is likely the nest of the Goblin Den. The iron door has been opened and the way forward cleared.\n"
  #EXAMINE
line940 = "You step up to the iron door and try to open it. The door doesn't budge. Of course it isn't that easy. You see that there is a KEY hole above the handle, and presume that there is a KEY somewhere around here to open the door.\n"
line940b = "You step up to the iron door and try to open it. The door doesn't budge. Of course it isn't that easy. You see that there is a KEY hole above the handle, and presume that there is a KEY somewhere around here to open the door.\nYou remember that you picked up an IRON KEY in the storage room. Would you like to try to OPEN the door, or BACK out?\n"
line941 = "You insert the IRON KEY and successfully unlock the door. The way forward is now clear. You can sense an evil presence in this direction, however. Are you sure you are prepared for whatever lies behind this door?\n"
line941b = "You decide now isn't the right time to try unlocking the door and put the IRON KEY away.\n"
line943 = "You attempt to move EAST but the way is blocked by a large iron door.\n"
  #SOUTH/WEST
line945 = "You look down into the pit to see below. Even the light from your LANTERN doesn't reach the bottom. You better not try going down there.\n"
  #JUMP/DIVE
line946 = "You take a few steps back to get a running start (might as well right?) and then leap over the edge, straight down into the pit. You instantly regret your life choices, but take solace in the fact that at least its almost ov...\n"
  #Goblin Den Final Room
line947 = "You take a few steps into a massive chamber deep within the cave; the Goblin QUEEN is waiting for you. The enormous Goblin lets out a terrible screech and leaps behind you, blocking the exit. There's only one way to make it out now. Prepare for combat!\n"
line948 = "You enter the defeated Goblin Queen's chamber. This is the end of the cave system.\n"
line949 = "The Goblin Queen takes her last breath and lets out a blood-curdling wail before being vanquished. You search what remains of her for anything interesting. Amongst her remains you find a DRAGON BONE KEY. These are said to be nigh indestructible and reserved for the most impenetrable of locks.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line950 = "The chamber is wet and filled with the remains of travelers picked off the roads. Most of the gear here has either rusted or rotted beyond any usefulness. The smell of Goblin is over-powering, making breathing unpleasant. You seem to have picked the cave clean of anything of value so it's probably time to leave.\n"
  #event
line951 = "You look at the Goblin Queen's remains and wonder how you're going to prove to the Smith you defeated her. You decide the most sensible thing would be to take one of her long, hairy fingers. You toss it into your pack and try to ignore the smell."


#10.BERRY******************************
line1001 = "You come upon a field of wild berries in the middle of the woods. The sun is shining brightly, and the air is sweet and fresh here.\n" #143
  #EXPLORE
line1002 = "An assortment of various wild berries are growing in the brambles and bushes surrounding you. A faint buzzing of bees can be heard. This place seems almost magical. You spot some incredibly juicy looking berries. EXAMINE for a closer look?\n"
  #EXAMINE
line1002b =  "The berries on this shrub have a faint red glow... Do you want to PICK some, or LEAVE them?\n"
line1002c = "You LEAVE the berries for the wildlife.\n"
line1003 = "You go to pick some berries but you are distracted; the sound of buzzing is getting louder. Before you know it, a Giant Bee Swarm assaults you!\n" #148
line1004 = "After finishing off the Giant Bee Swarm you take a moment to catch your breath before you go back to collecting berries. You recognize that you've found REZZBERRIES; the primary ingredient in POTIONS! You grab them all and squeeze them into some spare vials from your pack.\n" #149
line1005 = "An assortment of various wild berries are growing in the brambles and bushes surrounding you. You no longer hear any buzzing. You look to see if there are more REZZBERRIES, but it looks like they have all been picked.\n" #151
line1006 = "The REZZBERRIES have already been picked clean. You can wait here for them to regrow, but that might take a year... \n" #152
  
#11.SHRINE*******************************
line1101 = "You approach a dingy shrine tucked away in the woods. A Friar stops his prayer and slowly stands up to greet you.\n" #166
  #EXPLORE
line1102 = "Looking at the shrine the source of the glowing becomes quite apparent; a pair of large lanterns with flickering blue flames hang from the eaves of the shrine. The Friar is a stout older man with grey hair. He is looking as though he would desperately like to ask a favor of you. Maybe you should turn around and leave before he gets any ideas. Or you could try to SPEAK with him...\n" 
line1103 = "Looking at the shrine the source of the glowing becomes quite apparent; a pair of large lanterns with flickering blue flames hang from the eaves of the shrine. The Friar is a stout older man with grey hair. Now he's expecting your help...\n" 
line1104 = "Looking at the shrine the source of the glowing becomes quite apparent; a pair of large lanterns with flickering blue flames hang from the eaves of the shrine. The Friar is a stout older man with greying hair. He looks grateful that his late wife's PENDANT has been returned. You did a good thing bringing it back. And this sword was a nice bonus too...\n" 
  #SPEAK
line1105 = '"Adventurer, it is rare to see many travelers come to the shrine these days. Since the evil forces of Smeldar have begun roaming the woods it is much too dangerous to travel. I will still offer my services for as long as the holy flames stay lit. For a 35 GP donation you may PRAY here to restore your abilities (restore MP)"\n' 
line1106 = '"I have a favor to ask of you before you leave. My wife passed away many years ago shortly after we married and I would carry her PENDANT with me in remembrance. I lost it many years ago but find myself thinking about it lately. Please if you find my wifes PENDANT, would you bring it back to me?"\n' 
line1107 = '"Adventurer, it is good to see you are safe in your travels. I have great faith you can destroy the forces of Smeldar. I will still offer my services for as long as the holy flames stay lit. For a 35 GP donation you may PRAY here to restore your abilities. (Type PRAY to restore MP)"\n' 
line1108 = "You go to SPEAK to the Friar but before you can say a word he rushes towards you and snatches the PENDANT hanging from your pack.\n" 
line1109 = '"You found my wifes PENDANT! I thought I would never see it again. I will never forget this deed Adventurer. Please, accept this MESSER I once carried in my youth. I was too much of a coward to use it then... but perhaps you will be able to protect your loved ones with it."\n' 

#12.River******************************
line1201 = "At an intersection on the WEST path, just off the EAST bank of the Serpent River you come to an old stump. You take a seat while you decide your next actions.\n" 
  #EXPLORE
line1202 = "The Serpent River runs from the highlands SOUTH to the NORTH providing a natural border between the woods in the EAST and the lands WEST. The river is too deep to wade through and too wide and swift to safely swim across. The water is clear and you can see the shimmering river rocks lining the bottom of the river bed. You spot some fish fighting the current, heading upstream.\n" 
line1203 = "The Serpent River runs from the highlands SOUTH to the NORTH providing a natural border between the woods in the EAST and the lands WEST. The river is too deep to wade through and too wide and swift to safely swim across. The water is clear and you can see the shimmering river rocks lining the bottom of the River bed. You spot some fish fighting the current, heading upstream.\n\nYou can see the raft from earlier on the other side of the river.\n"
line1204 = "The Serpent River runs from the highlands SOUTH to the NORTH providing a natural border between the woods in the EAST and the lands WEST. The river is too deep to wade through and too wide and swift to safely swim across. The water is clear and you can see the shimmering river rocks lining the bottom of the river bed. You spot some fish fighting the current, heading upstream.\n\nThe raft is resting safely just off the River bank.\n"
line1206 = "The river is unable to be crossed. You'd probably drown if you tried." 
line1207 = "You attempt to cross the river and are immediately swept away by the current. You smash your head on a rock and go unconscious under the water.\n" 

#13.Waterfall*************************
line1301 = "Downstream from the river you come to a short waterfall. You stand near the bank of the river and look at the foaming water.\n" # 229
  #EXPLORE
line1302 = "The sound of the waterfall pouring down drowns out everything else around. The water here is foamy and harder to see through. You can spot fish jumping over the waterfall, presumably to reach their spawning grounds. You spot something stuck between some rocks near the edge of the plunge-pool. EXAMINE for a closer look?\n"
line1302b = "One fish doesn't look so lucky and appears to have gotten stuck. Looks like it's a tasty SALMON. You feel bad watching it struggle though. Should you TAKE it, SAVE it, or LEAVE it?\n" 
line1303 = "You TAKE the SALMON and put it in your pack. Really isn't this fishes' lucky day is it?\n" 
line1304 = "You dislodge the SALMON and set it free! The ungrateful fish carries on up the waterfall without thanking you. That was nice of you, even though that fish was a jerk." 
line1305 = "You leave the fish be. Best let nature sort itself out.\n" 
line1306 = "The sound of the waterfall pouring down drowns out everything else around. The water here is foamy and harder to see through. You can spot fish jumping over the waterfall, presumably to reach their spawning grounds. Doesn't look like any other fish are having trouble getting up the waterfall.\n" 
line1307 = "You take another look at the spot you saved the fish from. Looks like the SALMON did leave you a gift after all! You found a gold nugget worth 100GP!\n"
line1308 = "You take another look at the spot you found the fish. You don't find anything interesting.\n" 
  #SOUTH
line1309 = "The way SOUTH is blocked by the waterfall and a steep slope. No way through this way, unfortunately.\n" #247
  #WEST
line1310 = "It doesn't look possible to reach the WEST River bank from here. You'd probably drown if you tried.\n" #249
line1311 = "You attempt to cross the River and are immediately swept away by the current. You smash your head on a rock and go unconscious under the water.\n" #250
  #Waterfall cave 1
line1312 = "You stand at the entrance to a hidden cave behind the waterfall. You can hear the water pouring down behind you.\n"
    #EXPLORE
line1313 = "The cave walls are damp and jagged. Water drops steadily from the ceiling forming small pools on the ground. Looking down you can see pieces of crustaceans and shells smashed apart litter the floor here as well. The cave continues to the SOUTH, up a slanted path, and WEST, leading down underground.\n"
  #Waterfall cave 2
line1314 = "You find yourself standing in front of a large, seemingly endless pit. Fragments of light shine through tiny cracks in the ceiling, offering a dim view ahead."
    #EXPLORE
line1315 = "You take a look around the dimmy lit cave and see a pair of old rope bridges stretching across the pit ahead. Looking down the pit, you can't see the bottom, but you can hear water flowing below you. Still, it would be a pretty nasty fall...\n"
line1315b = "You take a look around the dimmy lit cave and see a pair of old rope bridges stretching across the pit ahead. The bridge on the EAST side has already collapsed and can no longer be crossed. Looking down the pit, you can't see the bottom, but you can hear water flowing below you. Still, it would be a pretty nasty fall...\n"
    #EXAMINE
line1316 = 'Before you are two rickety old rope bridges leading across a large chasm. Either looks like it may fall apart at any moment. Do you want to cross the bridge on the WEST, the EAST, or head BACK?\n' 
line1317 = 'You grab the sides of the rope bridge on the WEST and begin making your way across. Before you make it to the other side, you can feel the whole cave begin to shake. You head back to stable ground; soon after the opposite bridge collapses and you watch as the planks fall into the chasm. Luckily, the bridge you chose was sturdy enough to hold up. \n'
line1318 = 'You grab the sides of the rope bridge on the EAST and begin making your way across. Before you make it to the other side, you can feel the whole cave begin to shake. You try to head back to stable ground, but soon after the bridge you are standing on collapses and you begin falling into the chasm. Your life flashes before your eyes as you tumble down.\n'
line1218b = 'You land in some water, but find you are quickly swept away in the current. After a minute you manage to make it to the edge and climb back onto dry land.\n'
line1319 = "A massive pit stands between you and the way forward. You'll need to find a safe way across to continue...\n"
line1320 = 'You decide that the risk of falling is too great and step away from the bridges.\n'
line1321 = 'With the EAST bridge collapse, the WEST bridge is the only one left usable. Fortunately, it seems like it will have no trouble holding. Walking across should be safe.'
  #Waterfall cave 3
line1322 = 'You enter the deepest recesses of the cave. It is almost entirely dark here and the air here is cold and stale...\n'
    #EXPLORE
line1323 = 'You try to take a look around but you can hardly see anything. It seems like there may be something large up on a ridge just ahead of you...'
line1324 = ' Ahead on a small ridge you can see a massive serpent coiled around a chest. This must be the beast the old Captain spoke of...\n'
line1325 = "You try to take a look around but you can hardly see anything. Now that the serpent has been slain and it's treasure claimed, there probably isn't much here anyway...\n"
line1326 = "Taking a look around the chamber you can see more remains of various creatures and chunks of shedded skin. With the serpent defeated and its treasure claimed, there is little reason to stick around here any longer.\n"
    #EXAMINE
line1327 = "You try to take a look around but you can hardly see anything. You take a few steps forward, taking care in the dark. Despite your caution you stumble over a rock and fall forward. Instead of landing on the ground as expected, you crash into something... scaly. The serpent's body begins uncoiling from around its treasure and slams down attempting to crush you. You narrowly avoid the attack before drawing your own weapon!\n"
line1327a = "You try to take a look around but you can hardly see anything. You remember your lantern and turn it on. You spy the serpent on a ridge ahead. Do you want to ATTACK the serpent, or BACK away to safety?\n" 
line1327b = "You take a few steps towards the serpent. You creep up next to it and plunge your weapon into the beast! It lets out a horrific wail and readies itself for a counter attack!\n"
line1327c = "You decide you aren't ready to take on the serpent and carefully back up a bit.\n"
line1328 = "As the serpent draws its last breath you take a knife and pop out one of the massive, grapefruit sized eyes from the serpent's skull. You take a moment to gaze into the milky orb.\nYou realize the serpent was more blind than the Captain.\n\n You walk over to the chest the serpent had previously been guarding and bust open the heavily rusted lock. Inside you find a jar filled with a strange blue tinted grease. Perhaps a Smith can tell you more about its usage?..\n"
line1328a = "You try to take a closer look at your surroundings, but it's too dark to make out much... It might help if you had a light source."
line1328b = "You try to take a closer look at your surroundings, but it's too dark to make out much... You remember you have a LANTERN and turn it on!"
line1328c = "You search around but there isn't anything else valuable in here."
  #Waterfall cave 4
line1329 = "You find yourself standing on the bank of an underground river, deep within the cave. There's not much light down here.\n"
    #EXPLORE
line1330 = 'A small amount of light reaches this section of the cave from the entrance up to the EAST. The underground river in the WEST flows into a channel to the NORTH. The river moves much too quickly to safely swim in it, however.'

#14. LAKE*********************************
line1401 = "You make your way to Echobo Lake. The scene is quite serene as you watch the waves gently splash the shore. \n" #255
  #EXPLORE
line1402 = "The path here opens up to a much wider clearing in the woods. Up ahead to the NORTH is a boat house floating on the edge of the water off an old pier. The water here is just as clear as crystal and you can see schools of fish and aquatic vegetation growing on the lake bed. Just off the main path you can make out a worn dirt road leading EAST back into the woods. It doesn't look like it's seen much use in many years; the route back into the woods has been blocked by a giant flower growing over the road. EXAMINE for a better look?\n" #259
line1403 = "The path here opens up to a much wider clearing in the woods. Up ahead to the NORTH is a BOAT house floating on the edge of the water between two piers. The water here is just as clear as crystal and you can see schools of fish and aquatic vegetation growing on the lake bed. Just off the main path you can make out a worn dirt road leading EAST back into the woods. It doesn't look like it's seen much use in many years; the route back into the woods has been cleared though. Let's hope there aren't more evil plants that way.\n" #260
  #EXAMINE
line1404 = "The flower blocking the path is massive. It stands one and a half men tall and wide with dense foliage supporting it from below. The pink and black petals seem to form an image of a scowling woman. Doesn't look like there's anyway through here at this time.\n" #264
line1405 = "The flower blocking the path is massive. It stands one and a half men tall and wide with dense foliage supporting it from below. The pink and black petals seem to form an image of a scowling woman. Should you CUT it down and clear the path, or LEAVE it alone?\n" 
line1406 = "You take your AXE and begin chopping into the flower. Before you can get a second strike in, the flower starts to shift and uproot itself. Soon you realize that standing before you is a legendary Mandragora! It doesn't look too happy with you. \n" 
line1407 = "You LEAVE the flower alone for now. No sense in harming it right?\n" 
line1408 = "You stare at the remnants of the mangled Mandragora. The sap dripping from its broken stems and tattered petals make for a shockingly disturbing sight. You take notice of a pair of coiled thorns that could be used as bracers. You grab the THORN BRACERS and place them in your pack. Best to keep going and not think about how you murdered an endangered species.\n" 
line1409 = "You try to chop into the flower, but your AXE merely bounces off. You're going to need something sharper to get through this plant... Maybe you can find someone who can perform some maintenance on your AXE for you.\n" 
  #EAST
line1410 = "Your path is blocked by a massive flower. You've never seen anything like it in your travels before. EXAMINE for a closer look?\n" 
line1411 = "You continue on the cleared path and re-enter the woods.\n" 

line1414 = "Staring at the pristine lake water under the hot sun, you can't help yourself and dive in. You sink straight to the bottom. Forget you had too much gear on you?\n" 

#15.BOAT*******************************
line1501 = "You walk up to the docked BOAT house and see a Fisherwoman sitting with a pole on the dock staring out over the lake.\n" 
  #EXPLORE
line1502 = "The boat house is an old ship that appears to have been converted into a home. From the deck to the hull signs of years of repair can be seen all over. The Fisherwoman sees you standing there but doesn't acknowledge your presence; she is absorbed by her work, ready to spring the moment a fish bites the line. If she won't initiate a conversation, maybe you'll need to SPEAK to her first?\n" 
line1503 = "The BOAT house is clearly a boat that has been converted into a home. From the deck to the hull signs of years of repair can be seen all over. The Fisherwoman sees you standing there but doesn't acknowledge your presence; she is absorbed by her work, prepping food for her special dinner. If she won't initiate a conversation, maybe you should SPEAK to her first?\n" 
  #SPEAK
line1504 = '''"SHH! Don't  be so loud. You will scare away the fish. I have been trying to catch a SALMON all morning for my husband before he returns. My husband is a Lumberjack and needed to travel to his friend, a Smith, to commission a new AXE after he lost his running from a Bear. I wanted to have his favorite dish prepared for his return, but I am not having any luck. I don't know what I will do if I don't catch a SALMON soon! I am getting desperate. If you catch one, would you bring it back to me? I will make it worth your troubles, I promise."\n''' 
line1505 = '''"SHH! Don't be so loud. You will scare away the fish. I have been trying to catch a SALMON all morning for my husband before he returns. He needed to travel to his friend, a Smith, to commission a new AXE after he lost his running from a bear. It actually looked awfully like the one you are carrying... Anyway, I wanted to have his favorite dish prepared for his return, but I am not having any luck. I don't know what I will do if I don't catch a SALMON soon! I am getting desperate. If you catch one, would you bring it back to me? I will make it worth your troubles, I promise."\n''' 
line1506 = '"Is that a SALMON!? May I please have it?"  GIVE her the SALMON, or KEEP it?' #292
line1507 = '"Such a shame... Please come back if you change your mind."\n' 
line1508 = '''"Thank you so much! I thought I would never find one at this rate. Please, take this BUCKLER that once belonged to my brother. He left it with me when he laid down his arms and became a Friar. I have been using it as a fruit bowl, but you can probably get better use from it than me."\n''' 
line1509 = '"My husband will be thrilled when he returns home and sees his favorite meal being made. I wish I could thank you more kind Adventurer. Please stay safe on your quest!"\n' 
line1510 = '"Any luck finding a SALMON? If you can find one, please bring it back to me."\n' 
  #SOUTH
line1511 = "You start walking away from the BOAT house and continue down the lake shore SOUTH.\n" 
  #LEAVE
line1512 = "It doesn't appear there's anything notable in this direction. You'll need to go back SOUTH to EXIT.\n" 
#16.MUSHROOM**************************
line1601 = "You soon find yourself standing in a grove of mushrooms. It smells a little musty here.\n" 
  #EXPLORE
line1602 = "An assortment of mushrooms cover the ground and grow on the surrounding trees. Some of the caps are massive, larger than a man. The air is stale and musty here, and spores can be seen floating all around. You form a makeshift mask with some cloth to prevent breathing them in. Near the edge of the grove is a curious patch of fuzzy green caps. EXAMINE for a closer look?\n" 
line1603 = "The fuzzy green fungus form a dense covering across the floor they rest on. They smell a little like a wet Goblin. It looks like there might be something buried under them, but it's hard to tell right now...Maybe you should check back later.\n"
  #EXAMINE
line1604 = '''The fuzzy green fungus form a dense covering across the floor they rest on. They smell a little like a wet Goblin. It looks like there might be something buried under them; a pair of boots!\n\nYou take a look and see the boots and see they are still being worn. It looks like the owner has seen better days though; he's been dead for a while now. His body has been completely covered by mushrooms. Kind of gross. You see the corpse is clutching a golden medal and pry it out off, before putting it away in your pack.\n''' #316
line1604b = "Poor Jeremy. He presummably met his end doing what he loved; slaying goblins.\n"

#17.MEADOW**************************
line1701 = "You find yourself at a crossroads surrounded by flowers in a meadow. It's quite comforting.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line1702 = 'Flowers of every color can be found spread across the wide open field. The air here is refreshing. The warm sun and cool breeze make for a relaxing experience as you spend a few moments taking in the scenery. This would be a fantastic place to visit again once your quest is over.\nThe road NORTH is particularly aged and does not look like its seen any use years. To the EAST, the path appears to lead towards a massive OAK towering above the neighboring trees in the nearby woods. A sign off the side of the road points SOUTH and reads "VILLAGE". The BERRY patch can still be seen in the distance WEST of you.\n'

#18.VILLAGE**************************
line1801 = "You step into the center of a quiet VILLAGE tucked away on the edge of the woods. The townspeople wave hello, but carry about their days without paying you much mind.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line1802 = "The village is dotted with wattle and daub homes with wood shingles. You can see fields being prepared EAST and a tavern directly in front of you to the SOUTH. You can also see smoke rising in the WEST, appearing to come from a Smith's workshop. Sheep and chickens can be seen marching around the VILLAGE as if they were on patrol. The people here look rather relaxed. It would seem that the evil forces of Smeldar have yet to reach this far yet.\n"

#19.Smith**************************************
line1901 = """ You enter the workshop of the Village Smith. Sweat soon starts dripping from your brow as the heat of the forge envelopes you.\n\n"Ah, an adventurer. Nae mony come aroond 'ere gey often. Thae days ah mostly mak' horseshoes 'n' tools lik' mah mukker heres replacement AXE, bit ah used tae be th' ryle armorer! Fur th' richt price a'd be happy tae UPGRADE yer equipment. " \n"""
  #EXPLORE
line1902 = "The workshop is hot and smokey. Near the back, by the furnace, it is almost pitch black from accumulated soot. You wonder how anyone could manage to breath in here for any prolonged period. On a bench in the corner you spot a Lumberjack napping. The Smith carries on with his work while he waits to see if you will require his services.\n"
line1903 = "Aye, it looks like I've done everything I can for you and yer equipment.\n"
  #SPEAK
line1904 = """"If yi''ll need anythin' improved 'n' hae th' coin, ah will be happy tae hulp ye"\n """
line1905 = """"Ah see ye'v git something fur me tae keek at. Let's see whit we hae 'ere... Doesn't keek lik' ony grease a've seen afore. Tis ferr curious though. Mah auld master oot WAST shuid ken better than ah. His workshop is in th' hills o'er th' Serpents River. Hawp he's daein' weel..."\n """
line1906 = """"That AXE o' yers haes seen some better days. Tell ye whit.... Ah will wash up a' th' rust 'n' pat a fresh lip oan it if ye dae something fur me. Deep in th' cave up NORTH o' th' village 'ere lies a wretched cratur 'n' her vile spawn. They beats hae terrorized oor village fur far tae lang. Git rid o' th' Goblin Queen fur us 'n' a'd happily service yer AXE."\n """
line1906b = """"Th' Goblin Queen 'n' her hoard bide deep in th' cave north o' th' village. Dinnae even fash trying tae mak' it thro' wi'oot a source o' light. If ye dinnae hae something, a'd check th' shop in th' Royal City fur something... "\n """
line1907 = """"Whit hae ye git thare fur me..? A finger?! fae th'  Goblin Queen ye say? Ah ne'er asked fur proof bit ah appreciate yer dedication! haha! Gimme yer AXE 'n' ah will fix it up fur ye as promised."\n\n"'Ere ye gang! a' cleaned up 'n' sharp enough tae fell an oak in three swings! Reminds me o' yin o' mah auld pieces actually... Anyway 'ere ye gang. Guid luck oan yer quest! Mind, a'm 'ere if ye ever need tae UPGRADE yer gear! "\n """
line1907b = """"Awready gubbed her ye say? haha! Ah knew ye wur th' best body fur th' jab! Gimme yer AXE 'n' ah will fix it up fur ye as promised."\n\n"'Ere ye gang! a' cleaned up 'n' sharp enough tae fell an oak in three swings! Reminds me o' yin o' mah auld pieces actually... Anyway 'ere ye gang. Guid luck oan yer quest! Mind, a'm 'ere if ye ever need tae UPGRADE yer gear! "\n """
#20.OAK*****************************************
line2001 = "You approach a massive OAK standing several stories above the surrounding trees with a trunk as wide as a small city.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line2002 = "It's said that massive trees like this house the spirit of the woods they reside in. This Great OAK must have stood here for over a thousand years; it's easily the oldest tree in these woods. There doesn't appear to be any other paths around the OAK, however you do spy a rope ladder. You should EXAMINE it for a closer look.\n"
  #EXAMINE
line2003 = "You come closer to the OAK and take a look at the rope ladder dangling from the tree. Looking up you can see the ladder goes past the canopy. It seems sturdy enough to hold your weight without trouble; you could probably CLIMB it.\n"
line2004 = "You grab either end of the ladder and start making your way up, carefully.\n"
line2005 = "You decide that climbing the OAK is an unnecessary risk and walk away from the tree.\n"


#21.HIVE*********************************
line2101 = "While you climb you can hear a familiar buzzing coming from above. As you make your way further up the ladder your hands start to become slightly sticky.\n\nAfter climbing several stories up the rope ladder, you reach the top and pull yourself up. You find yourself standing inside a Giant Bee Hive. Honey oozes from the walls and Bee larvae can be seen wriggling inside cells. It isn't long before the Bees notice an intruder has entered their hive. You brace for combat as a stream of Bees head directly for you.\n"
line2101b = "\nMore bees are approaching!\n"
line2102 = "You crush every last Bee that comes your way, pushing deeper into the hive just to spite the furious, bumbling pests. Before you make it far, the Queen Bee erupts from her chamber and strikes at you with her massive body. She thrashes about the hive in desperation; she will not give up until one of you is dead.\n"
line2103 = "The Queen Bee is vanquished; her subjects recognizing the recent regicide committed here immediately begin to flee. Congratulations on causing the colony to collapse.\nThe ROYAL JELLY of the Queen Bee is said to have the ability to enhance the potency of POTIONS. Even the smallest drop has a huge effect. You search the hive for ROYAL JELLY and manage to find enough to fill a bottle. This should last you your entire journey! There's nothing else here, so you begin descending the ladder.\n"
line2104 = "You find yourself standing back inside the giant hive. The Bees have all abandoned the hive since the death of their queen. Maybe they'll find a new home and set up a bee-mocracy?\n"
  #EXPLORE
line2105 = "You have another look around in case you missed something. After having another look you find a cell of honey emitting a soft red glow. EXAMINE for a closer look?\n"
  #/EXAMINE
line2105b = "You approach the cell of glowing honey and give it a taste... It reminds you of REZZBERRIES! This honey probably has the same healing effects, so you fill some vials for later.\n"
line2106 = "You triple check and come up short on anything. Looks like you got it all on your last sweep. Time to climb down.\n"
line2106b = "You look inside the cell you found the glowing honey in. You got every drop the first time; now it's empty.\n"
  #LEAVE
line2108 = "You CLIMB down the ladder once more.\n"

#22.FARM************************************
line2201 = "Sitting on a small hill overlooking the fields, you step up to an old FARM house.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line2202 = "Surrounding the FARM house are fields housing various crops and livestock. The scent of manure baking in the sun fills your nose.\nAn old Farmer sits on the house's porch and motions you over to SPEAK.\n"
  #SPEAK
line2203 = """ "Well now if it isn't an honest to god Adventurer here in these boondocks. We don't see many travelers of any sort around here. Had one that visited here fairly often; last time he came by he was ranting about slaying Goblins and checking out some rumors of a new species sighted in the woods EAST of Echobo Lake. Hasn't been by since though... If you see him, give the lad my regards.\n\nNow while you're here I have a favor to ask you. One of my prized pigs is sick and needs a SPECIAL FEED to sell in the city. If I leave there will be no one left who can look after my pig and she'll surely pass, but she wont get better without the feed... If you can get the feed for me I would be deeply grateful" (Type YES or NO.)\n """
line2204 = """ "Ah well, please let me know if you change your mind... Oh... poor Hamila..."\n """
line2204b = """ "Have you changed your mind then? Are you willing to pick up the SPECIAL FEED for me?"\n """
line2205 = """ "Thank you so much! Here is some GP to help cover the cost. I have more here when you return.\nPlease hurry if you can! I don't want my poor piggy to suffer any longer..."\n """
line2206 = """ "Thank you so much for bringing me the feed. You came just in time. I'm sure Hamila will make a swift recovery now. There isn't much I have to offer, but I tell you what, you can have my old HAMMER!" \n"""
line2207 = """ "Haven't gotten the feed yet? That's fine... Hamila is hanging in there..." \n"""
line2208 = """ "Why if it isn't my favorite Adventurer. After what you've done for me you are always welcome in these parts!" \n"""

#24.WITCH****************************
line2401 = 'You come to a dingy cabin in the middle of a small clearing. A crooked old woman is hunched over tending to a small garden.'
 #EXPLORE
line2402 = 'The cabin is surrounded by old, twisted trees and stumps. Outside the cabin a wrought iron cauldron sits above a fire, its contents bubbling to the brim. The old woman is dressed in dark dusty robes and a pointed hat, bent slightly near the tip. '
 #SPEAK
line2403 = """"I've been waiting for you Adventurer... come closer, I wont bite! I've seen you coming and would like to offer you my services, hehehe! If you can bring me 5 each of PLANT PARTS, MONSTER PARTS, RARE MONSTER PARTS, and FAE DUST, I can whip you up some incredible tonics unlike anything you'll find elsewhere! Hehehe! You'll need a CRAFTING POUCH if you want to carry the materials... I'm sure you can find one somewhere in that stuffy CITY."\n """
line2404 = """"Already back? I hope you brought me the ingredients I requested. I need 5 each of PLANT PARTS, MONSTER PARTS, RARE MONSTER PARTS, and FAE DUST. Hehehe!"\n """
line2405 = """"Wonderful! Let me see what you have brought me... Ah yes, these will do nicely. Let me just mix these in my cauldron here... Hehehe!"\n"""
line2406 = """"Now, which tonic would you like me to brew for you? Hehehe!"\n"""
line2407 = """"Here you go Adventurer! Use it well. Hehehe!"\n """
line2408 = """"You haven't gathered the ingredients yet? Hehehe! Take your time."\n """
line2409 = """"Ah, it's you again Adventurer! Feel free to stop by anytime you need some potions brewed. Hehehe! (Type CRAFT to open brewing menu)"\n """
line2410 = """"Go on now, first time's free hehehe!"\n """


#25.THICKET**************************
line2501 = "You push your way through the dense underbrush of the forest. The trees here are gnarled and twisted, their branches reaching out like skeletal fingers. The air is thick with the scent of damp earth and decaying leaves. You can hear the distant sound of crows beyond a dense thicket.\n"
line2502 = "You push your way through the dense underbrush of the forest. The trees here are gnarled and twisted, their branches reaching out like skeletal fingers. The air is thick with the scent of damp earth and decaying leaves. You've cleared the path to the NORTH.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line2503 = "Deep in the heart of this dark forest, you can feel a palpable sense of dread. The trees seem to close in around you, their branches twisting into grotesque shapes. The way forward has been blocked by a wall of thorns and dense foliage. If only there was some way to chop these down...\n"
line2504 = "Deep in the heart of this dark forest, you can feel a palpable sense of dread. The trees seem to close in around you, their branches twisting into grotesque shapes. The dense wall of thorns has been chopped down, opening the way forward.\n"
  #EXAMINE
line2505 = "A dense wall of thorns blocks the way forward. Smeldar's Tower looms in the distance, just beyond the thicket... If only there was some way to chop down these branches...\n"
line2506 = "A dense wall of thorns blocks the way forward. Smeldar's Tower looms in the distance, just beyond the thicket... You could easily take care of these branches with your AXE. CUT them down or LEAVE them alone?\n"
line2507 = "You take hold of your AXE and begin hacking away at the branches. Before long the entire path is open. You are one step closer to reaching Smeldar's Tower!\n"
line2507b = " You remember that thing you forgot to do earlier and decide to leave the branches alone for now....\n"
line2507c = "You take hold of your AXE and begin hacking away at the branches. Unfortunately the branches are far too thick and dense for your AXE to handle. You'll need something stronger to cut through this wall...\n"
line2507d = "You marvel at your extraordinary ability to clear unwanted foliage. You consider starting a career in landscaping once this is all over.\n"
  #NORTH
line2508 = "You attempt to continue NORTH, but are stopped by a wall of thorny branches. If only you had a way to cut them down...\n"
line2509 = "You attempt to continue NORTH, but are stopped by a wall of thorny branches. Maybe you could use your AXE to cut them down?\n"


#26.ROTTING WOODS********************************************
line2601 = "As you continue you on the path you find yourself standing in mud surrounded by half rotted trees.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line2602 = 'The plants here are all rotting and sickly. A parasitic fungus infects all of the trees here. It would seem the mushrooms in the SOUTH are aggressively spreading here thanks to the humid air. Loud croaking can be heard coming from the way NORTH.  Looking EAST you see a mushroom of such tremendous size it looks like it might collapse under its own weight at any time... A breeze coming from the WEST carries with it the scent of soil and sulfur and you spy a broken sign standing crooked off the path. All you can read is:\nBew...\nOgr...\n'
line2603 = 'The plants here are all rotting and sickly. A parasitic fungus infects all of the trees here. It would seem the mushrooms in the SOUTH are aggressively spreading here thanks to the humid air. Loud croaking can be heard coming from the way NORTH.  Looking EAST you see a massive mushroom has fallen over clearing a path deeper into the woods. A breeze coming from the WEST carries with it the scent of soil and sulfur and you spy a broken sign standing crooked off the path. All you can read is:\nBew...\nOgr...\n'
  #Rotting Woods East
line2604 = 'You move through the rotting forest and continue down the trail. The stale, musty air is almost suffocating, however you keep pushing forward.'
  #EXPLORE
line2605 = "Your feet squish across the muddy ground, covered in soggy brown leaves and patches of fuzzy mold. The mushrooms growing on the surrounding tree trunks come in all sorts of shapes, sizes and colors. It's hard to admire their looks though while choking on the spores hanging in the air. You can see a faint blue glow coming from the NORTH here..."
line2606 = "Your feet squish across the muddy ground covered in soggy brown leaves and patches of fuzzy mold. The mushrooms growing on the surrounding tree trunks come in all sorts of shapes, sizes and colors. It's hard to admire their looks though while choking on the spores hanging in the air. You no longer see the glow coming from the NORTH."
  #Hidden Shrine
line2607 = "You approach a run down shrine in the middle of the woods. Rotten wood beams hold up what remains of the nearly collapsed roof. At the center of the shrine a bright blue flame flickers within a large rusted brazier."
line2608 = "You approach a run down shrine in the middle of the woods. Rotten wood beams hold up what remains of the nearly collapsed roof. At the center of the shrine a large rusted brazier sits empty."
  #EXPLORE
line2609 = "The shrine is in a state of total disrepair. It would seem it was abandoned many years ago, and the woods have been working to reclaim it. Curiously, the surrounding rot doesn't appear to have taken hold within the shrine. Perhaps the flame has been able to keep it at bay...(EXAMINE flame?)"
line2610 = "The shrine is in a state of total disrepair. It would seem it was abandoned many years ago, and the woods have been working to reclaim it. Curiously, the surrounding rot doesn't appear to have taken hold within the shrine. Without the DIVINE FLAME will this place be overcome by the rot as well?.. "
  #EXAMINE
line2611 = """You step into the shrine and take a look at the deep blue flame flickering within the brazier. It has a calming effect on you as you gaze upon it. You open your LANTERN towards the brazier and in a flash the flame jumps into your LANTERN. Now, with the blue flame now flickering within, you've obtained the power of the BLUE FLAME LANTERN!\nAS you begin to step away from the shrine, you begin to hear a disturbing cackle come from behind.\n"How precious. Another fool has come thinking that my flame is theirs to take... It has been some time since I've had such a foolish visitor."\nYou swing your head around behind you and from the darkness you see something slowly descend from the ceiling. You hold up your LANTERN and reveal a Spider-Lady hanging from a cord of silk.\n"My apologies... Normally I would be a more entertaining host... but it's been so long... and I am so hungry!"\n """
line2612 = "With the Spider-Ladies' demise, you can now claim the DIVINE FLAME for your own. You pick up your LANTERN and exit the shrine. Your adventure continues!"
line2613 = "You peak back inside the old abandoned shrine. Without the flames protection the rot has quickly started to take hold. Mold has started growing on the wood beams and fungus has sprung from the dark corners. It won't be long until the whole shrine is consumed."

#27.ROTTEN SWAMP********************************************
  #Swap 1
line2701 = "You step into a murky swamp. Thick gas hangs in the air between the rotting trees sticking up from the mud and muk.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line2702 = 'All around you are rotting trees covered in moss. The swamp is filled with a  thick, brown sludge that is hard to call water, or even mud. It smells like rotting eggs and decaying leaves here. Further WEST the path continues deeper into the swamp.\n'

  #Swamp 2
line2703 = "You continue walking through the swamp until you reach a 3-way junction. You try not to stand in one spot too long so you don't sink in the mud. \n"
  #EXPLORE
line2704 = 'The ground here is wet and muddy. You take extra care as to where you walk to avoid becoming stuck. You see the path continues deeper into the swamp going SOUTH and WEST. Several trees can be seen knocked over; something (or somethings) very big lives here.\n'

  #Swamp 3
line2705 = "You come to a 3-way junction deep in the swamp. It is starting to feel like you are being watched...\n"
  #EXPLORE
line2706 = 'You look around and try to see through the thick swamp gas. A deep pool of sludge lies to the WEST. You see signs something was recently dragged across here to the NORTH. The path through the swamp also continues EAST and SOUTH from here.\n'

  #Swamp 4
line2707 = "You step into a small clearing in the swamp with some more stable ground. In front of you are two wooden chests.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line2708 = '''The stench of the swamp isn't quite as strong here, but is still very unpleasant. Directly ahead are two wooden chests that have been dragged over to the middle of the clearing. It looks like whatever was moving these left them in a hurry. EXAMINE for a closer look?\n'''
  #EXAMINE
line2709 = 'You walk up to the two chests. Both appear to be tightly shut, but neither is locked. Would you like to check out the chest on the LEFT, RIGHT, or BACK away and leave them be?\n'
line2710 = 'You walk up to the two chests. The one on the right appears to be tightly shut, but is not locked. The chest on the left has already been opened. Would you like to check out the chest on the RIGHT or BACK away and leave it be?\n'
line2711 = 'You walk up to the two chests. The one on the left appears to be tightly shut, but is not locked. The chest on the right has already been opened. Would you like to check out the chest on the LEFT or BACK away and leave it be?\n'
line2712 = 'You walk up to the two chests. Both chests have been opened and are now sitting there, empty.\n'
line2712b = 'You walk up to the left-side chest. OPEN, SMASH, or BACK away?\n'
line2712c = 'You walk up to the right-side chest. OPEN, SMASH, or BACK away?\n'
line2713 = 'You open the chest on the LEFT and go to examine the contents. Before you are able to, a noxious gas from within the chest fills your nostrils and makes you sick. An OOZING SLIME pours from the chest and begins to attack!.\n'
line2713b = 'You smash open the chest on the LEFT releasing a noxious gas that quickly dissipates. Fortunately you were able to avoid breathing much in. Soon after an OOZING SLIME pours from the chest and begins to attack!.\n'
line2714 = 'The OOZING SLIME defeated, you go to check the chest again... unfortunately it looks like you just killed the only contents...\n'
line2715 = 'You open the chest on the RIGHT and examine the contents. You find a MOUTH-PIECE!\n'
line2715b = '''You smash open the chest on the RIGHT and examine the contents. You find a MOUTH-PIECE! Luckily you didn't damage it. You should really be more careful you know.\n'''
line2716 = 'You combine the BROKEN HORN with the MOUTH-PIECE. You now have the COMPLETE HORN!\n'

  #swamp 5
line2717 = "The path leads to a wide cross road in the middle of the swamp. You stand on a fallen log in middle of the area to get your feet out of the muk.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line2718 = "The paths that lie NORTH, EAST, SOUTH, and WEST are masked by a thick cloud of swamp gas. It is hard to tell what is in any direction from here. The fallen log lies next to a large stone with unnatural markings carved onto one side. It may be some sort of writing, but you've never seen any language like this before. Carved into the rock next to the markings are a pair of crude arrows pointing NORTH and SOUTH.\n" 
  #swamp 6
line2719 = "You come to a bend in the path and sit on a tree stump next to a large pool of swamp water while you plan your next steps.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line2720 = "The path here bends from NORTH to WEST, curving past a putrid pool of swamp water in the EAST and SOUTH. A dead fish floats past you while you look at the water. Probably not a good sign. You see a set of tracks in the SOUTH-WEST corner of the area. They look like they were made by something with hooves that came by recently...\n"
line2721 = "Maybe it's the swamp gas going to your head, but that water is looking pretty tasty right now... You reach down and take a sip. You aren't feeling so good...\n"
line2722 = "You continue to stare at the water and think to yourself how much like a chocolate jelly pond it looks like. You soon find yourself consumed by thoughts telling you to jump in. You eventually break and dive straight into the pool! Something grabs your leg and you are immediately dragged down to the bottom.\n"
 #swamp 7
line2723 = 'Deeper into the swamp you begin to hear a chorus of frogs ribbiting as you approach a murky pond.\n'
  #EXPLORE
line2724 = 'Surrounding you is a stagnant pond of filthy water. Dragonflies buzzing around and the loud ribbitting of frogs form a surprisingly pleasant symphony. You take a moment to enjoy the sounds, forgetting for a moment that you are enveloped in the smell of rotten eggs. \n'
line2725 = 'You start ribbiting back in harmony with the frogs. After a moment you realize the noises from the swamp have ceased and it is now silent. Bubbles begin to appear at the surface of the pond; slowly an algae covered log raises from the water. A massive red frog sitting on the log opens its mouth and spits out a GOLD RING in front of you. As soon as you grab the ring the log begins to lower back into the water and the sounds of the swamp return.\n'
line2726 = 'You try to mimic the frog-siren song again, but nothing else happens...\n'
  #swamp 8
line2727 = 'You step onto a muddy peninsula deep within the swamp. A chill fills the air here and all the sounds of the swamp cease.\n'
  #EXPLORE
line2728 = 'The smell of death lingers around you. You can see bones with the meat picked clean and shattered weapons and armor littering the ground. Something ferocious lives here, and it is not likely to be pleased with your presence. This seems to be the deepest reaches of the swamp...\n'
line2729 = 'The smell of death lingers around you. You can see bones with the meat picked clean and shattered weapons and armor littering the ground. Something ferocious lives here, and it is not likely to be pleased with your presence. This seems to be the deepest reaches of the swamp... The Frog-Man said this would be the place to PLAY the horn to summon an audience with the Ogre Chief.\n'
line2730 = 'The Ogre Chief is gone, but the swamp is still a dangerous place. It would be unwise to continue hanging around here without cause. A fallen tree trunk forms a bridge leading to the EAST.\n'
  #special
line2731 = 'You begin playing the horn, letting out a note that echoes across the swamp. Soon you can hear another horn blowing in the distance, returning your call. Out of the swamp gas a small barge emerges. When the barge reaches the shore a hulking mass of muscle and flesh steps off.\n'
line2732 = 'The Ogre Chief looks down at you; you can see the anger burning in his eyes. Your intrusion will not go unpunished.\n'
line2733 = 'The Ogre Chief looks down at you; "What offering have you brought for me puny one?"\n'
line2734 = 'You look in your bag and see you have the WAFFLE dropped from the donkey. Would you like to GIVE the Ogre Chief the WAFFLE or KEEP it?\n'
line2735 = 'The Ogre Chief takes the waffle and nods at you silently. He soon turns around and returns to his barge. You notice something fall from his key ring as he is getting back on his vessel. You pick it up and discover it is a GILDED DRAGON BONE KEY. Thinking that this is an important item you quickly place it in your bag.\n\n Before you carry on you decide to take a quick moment to rest and lean up against a dead tree. The trunk suddenly gives way and topples over, forming a bridge to the EAST. Convenient!\n'
line2736 = 'You reach into your bag and pull out your middle finger. The Ogre Chief is enraged by your insult and begins thrashing around wildly. Have fun with that.\n'
line2737 = 'You play the horn once again. This time there is no response.\n'
line2738 = "After a fierce battle with the Ogre Chief, you land a finishing blow and the chief takes his last breath. As he falls to the ground you let out a sigh of relief. After searching his body you find a GILDED DRAGON BONE KEY. Thinking that this is an important item you quickly place it in your bag.\n\n You take a quick look around before you leave and notice that during the heat of battle a dead tree must have fallen over forming a bridge leading EAST. Convenient!\n"
#28. Frog MArsh
line2801 = 'You step onto a series of piers stretching across a reed filled marsh. A Frog-Man sits on a rocking chair outside a hut built right over the marsh. It looks like he is interested in SPEAKING.\n'
  #EXPLORE
line2802 = 'The marsh is filled with the sounds of creatures roaming the area. Herons can be spotted fishing further across the water and tadpoles can be seen hiding under the piers. You take a minute to watch the dragonflies dancing over the reeds sprouting from the water. A cheerful Frog-Man sits outside a quaint hut built over the water, beckoning you over. The path across the piers continues EAST from here.\n'
  #Speech
line2803 = """"Why if it isn't an honest to goodness Adventurer in my marsh! It's quite the honor to have visitors way out in these parts. The Ogre tribe to the WEST has been causing all kinds of trouble lately, though their chief hasn't been seen in some time... Say, if you're looking to take on the Ogre Chief I've got some information you'll be needing. My grandpappy told me when I was just a tadpole that the Ogre tribesman would PLAY a loud horn as a challenge against the current chief. No Ogre would dare ignore such a call."\n"This BROKEN HORN here is missing the MOUTH PIECE, but if you can find a way to fix it you could try PLAYING it to summon the Ogre Chief for a battle!"\n"""
line2804 = """"Look who's back to visit! Come to hear another of grandpappy's stories? My grandpappy said years back he was in the swamps to the WEST when he heard the most peculiar song. He said he started singing along when suddenly someone popped up from behind and scared him! He said he dropped his GOLD RING in the swamp and never found it. Maybe whoever spooked him picked it up and still has it.\n """
line2805 = """"Welcome back! Come to hear more stories? My grandpappy used to always tell me to run from bunnies. I dont know why he was so scared of them. They seem pretty cute to me."\n """
line2806 = """""Hey there Adventurer! Can't get enough of my granpappy's stories? He always said there were Dwarfs living SOUTH of the swamp, past the forest of the Fae, but that one always seemed far-fetched. Grandpappy never lied about anything else though, so maybe he was right?"\n """
#29.Fairy Circle
line2901 = "Making your way through the Mushroom Grove, you find a circle of mushrooms in a field of strange purple flowers.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line2902 = "Sunbeams penetrate the canopy here illuminating the circle of mushrooms and many flowers that cover the ground. You recall that these circles of mushrooms are known as Fairy Circles, but you have never seen or heard of the strange purple flowers that grow here. There is an especially dense patch of them in the center of the Fairy Circle. You feel drawn towards them...\n"
line2903 = "Sunbeams penetrate the canopy here illuminating the circle of mushrooms and many flowers that cover the ground. You recall that these circles of mushrooms are known as Fairy Circles, but you have never seen or heard of the strange purple flowers that grow here. There is an especially dense patch of them in the center of the Fairy Circle. A fairy with the appearance of a young man sits in the center of the circle.\n"
line2904 = "Sunbeams penetrate the canopy here illuminating the now shriveled circle of mushrooms. The purple flowers that were once growing here have died with the Dark Fairy Prince. This place has lost its magical presence, but it feels much safer than before.\n"
  #EXAMINE
line2905 = "You step into the Fairy Circle and kneel over to examine the flowers in the middle. You don't find anything of interest at this time..."
line2906 = """You step into the Fairy Circle and kneel over to examine the flowers in the middle.\n"Why hello there. Can you please help me?.."\nYou look up and see a young man sitting in the Fairy Circle you previously hadn't noticed. He has pointed ears and a flowing purple robe the same color as the flowers surrounding you. It takes a moment before you realize he has a pair of translucent wings.\n"I am the prince of Fairies. I was trapped here ages ago by a wicked Dark Fae that sought to overthrow my kingdom... I am quite weak now... Please, if you can defeat Dark Fae some of my power should return to me. As my magic returns I should be able to reward you for your efforts. Come back to me to check to see how many Dark Fae you have defeated." """
line2907 = "You see the Fairy Prince calmly sitting in the Fairy Circle. It looks like he may be confined within it..."
line2908 = "The Dark Fairy Prince has been defeated. The flowers have all wilted and the Fairy Circle mushrooms have begun to shrivel. Hopefully the evil Fae is gone for good this time..."
  #speak
line2909 = """"Thank you for coming. I can feel my power starting to return. Take this gift as my thank you for your help. Please, continue to defeat more Dark Fae. I am still feeling very weak..."\n """
line2910 = """"Thank you for coming. I can feel my power returning. Take this gift as my thank you for your help. Please, continue to defeat more Dark Fae. I need more power..."\n """
line2911 = """"Thank you for coming... You have done well helping my power return to me. Now for your reward... As a gift I will impart with you this knowledge; I am not the Fairy Prince. No, I am the Prince of the Dark Fae! You have foolishly helped me regain my strength! Smeldar will be quite pleased to hear of my return! I will be granted another army and I shall be the lord of all Fae! Now be good and surrender. If you do, I will reward you with a final gift; a quick death! HEHEHEHE!"\n"""
line2912 = "The Dark Fairy Prince lets out a shriek before dissipating into nothing. The flowers all around begin to instantly wither away and the Fairy Circle shrivels up. On the ground where the Dark Fairy Prince had been sitting lies a CRYSTAL NECKLACE. You take it and add it to your inventory."
#30. Grassy Plains******************
line3001 = "You find yourself in a large grass field stretching across the NORTH of the kingdom.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line3002 = "A cool breeze blows in from the NORTH carrying with it the taste of salt and providing relief from the sun's rays beating down from above. In the distance to the EAST you can see a mountain range, and SOUTH you see the border of the Rotted Woods. In the WEST lies the Frog Marsh.\n"
#31. Foot Hills
line3101 = "You reach the Foot Hills of the great northern mountain range. You stand in the shade of the mountains while you plot your course.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line3102 = "The Foot Hills lead up into the great northern mountains. Travelers are warned to avoid attempting to travel across the range at all costs; the paths are too steep and are prone to collapse under foot. Few have even tempted the journey, and far fewer lived to tell the tale. The sea can be spotted in the distance NORTH of here, and the plains continue to stretch out WEST.\n"
#32. Northern Coast
line3201 = "Waves crash against the shore as you approach the Northern Coast. You pause for a moment to admire the sea.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line3202 = "Gulls fly overhead and hermit crabs scuttle across the warm sands. A coral reef teeming with life can be seen through the crystal clear sea water. For just a moment you forget your worries and are able to relax. When you finish taking in the sights and smells of the seas you begin plotting your course once again. The beach continues to the EAST, and behind you to the SOUTH the Grassy Plains. WEST of here you can spot the entrance to a bustling Harbor Town.\n"
#33. Shipwreck
line3301 = "You approach a Shipwreck on the beach of the Northern Coast. Pieces of the wreckage litter the shore."
  #EXPLORE
line3302 = "Just off the coast the bow of a large ship can be seen poking up out of the water. Shattered planks, barrels, and crates can be spotted all along the beach. Although it looks like this ship crashed here quite some time ago, it looks like some of the cargo may have survived and there may still be of something of value to EXAMINE...\n"
line3303 = "Just off the coast the bow of a large ship can be seen poking up out of the water. Shattered planks, barrels, and crates can be spotted all along the beach. The contents have been picked clean at this point. Anything valuable the ship was carrying is gone now.\n"
  #EXAMINE
line3304 = "You look around at the cargo strewn about the beach. Do you want to search it for anything valuable? Type YES or NO.\n"
line3305 = "You decide it would be better to leave the cargo alone. No idea what could be in there.\n"
line3306 = "You take a look around the wreckage to see if there is anything useful.\n"
line3307 = "Suddenly something jumps out from the debris and attacks!\n"
line3308 = "You open up a crate and rummage through the contents. Within you find a small jewel box with some gems worth 300 GP! Looks like there are also a couple of POTIONS inside. What a lucky find!\n"
line3309 = "It doesn't seem like there is anything else worth searching around here.\n"
#34. Harbor Town****************************
line3401 = "You enter the Harbor Town and make your way to the town center.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line3402 = 'Cobblestone streets weave through the cottages and shops throughout the town. NORTH of here you can see the harbor and the local markets. From here you can also see a large sign in the WEST that says "Harbor Inn". The people of the town pay little attention to you; travelers must be a frequent sight in a port city such as this one.\n'
  #Harbor Temple
line3403 = "You step into a small temple on the EAST side of the Harbor town. Directly ahead lies an alter with a sign requesting a small donation of 35 GP to PRAY.\n"
line3404 = "Two rows of pews flank the gold trimmed rug leading up to the altar. At either side of the altar stand two lanterns with blue flames flickering within. There are a few devotees sitting at the pews with their heads down, quietly saying prayers. A pair of monks can be seen tending to their monastic duties; they are too busy to SPEAK.\n"
  #SPEAK
line3405 = """"Sorry, we still have quite a few chores we need to finish and don't have time to speak. If you would like to PRAY and receive blessings, we kindly ask that you provide a charitable donation to the box at the altar."\n """
line3406 = """"Please, we are very busy... If you would like to PRAY and receive blessings, just drop a donation in the box at the altar."\n """
line3407 = """You try talking to the monks, but they completely ignore you. Jerks.\n """
#35. Docked Ship
line3501 = """"You step to the end of the docks and walk up to an old anchored galleon. An old man with an elegant captain hat steps down from the ship to greet you.\n"Come here! I be looking fer an Adventurer and ye looks like the perfect one fer the job!"\n """
line3501b = """"You step to the end of the docks and walk up to an old anchored galleon. An old man with an elegant captains hat steps down from the ship to greet you.\n"""
  #EXPLORE
line3502 = 'The old galleon is a fine vessel, despite the signs of many years of wear and maintenance. The Captain looks quite proud of his ship. The Captain is as worn as his vessel; you spy several missing digits on top of his peg leg, eye-patch, and his gapped smile. He seems to have lived quite a full life on the sea.\n'
  #SPEAK
line3503 = """"Many years ago when I was jus' a young lad workin' the river, me eye was taken from me by a wicked serpent o' the falls. The beast left me half blind fer the better years o' me life, 'n I intend t' get me revenge afore I croak.  If ye agree I will teach ye where the secret passage in the falls lies. O' course ye will be rewarded handsomely..."\nDo you agree to help the old Captain, YES or NO."""
line3503b = """"'Ave ye found yer courage 'n come t' help?" Do you agree to help the old Captain, YES or NO.\n """
line3504 = """"Blisterin' barnacles! I knew ye we be right scallywag fer the job! Now t' get into the falls ye simply take this hidden route here... When ye make it inside ye'll needs t' enter the serpents chamber in the deepest reaches o' the cave. The beast guards a booty wit' its mighty life; ye're more than welcome t' it once the wretched creature has been slain. Bring me the SERPENTS EYE 'n I will pay ye a kings ransom."\n """
line3505 = """"Blast ye! Ye're a yellow-bellied cur if I ever saw one. Come back once ye've grown a spine!"\n """
line3506 = """"'Ave ye brought me the SERPENTS EYE? No? Then wha' are ye doin' wastin' me time! Go out 'n finish the job!"\n """
line3507 = """"I see ye've brought the SERPENTS EYE wit' ye! Har har har! I knew ye had it in ye! Now this ole sea dog can rest easy. Jus' as promised here's yer reward."\n """
line3508 = """"Back t' visit this ole Cap'n? Ye did a mighty fine job defeatin' the serpent fer me. I be forever grateful. If anyone can scuttle the ol' fool Smeldar 'twill be ye! Har har har." """
#36.Alchemist 
line3601 = """You walk into the Alchemist shop and step up to the shop counter. A curious man with pointed ears pops up from behind the counter and welcomes you in.\n"Welcome Adventurer! I can tell you are well traveled. SPEAK to me and we can discuss a special service I offer folks like you."\n """
  #EXPLORE
line3602 = 'All around you are shelves filled with glass bottles, vials, and jars filled with an assortment of liquids of varying colours and viscosities as well as strange alchemical ingredients, many you have never seen and are completely unable to identify. A pair of cauldrons can be spotted in the back behind the counter on opposite sides of the room.\n'
  #SPEAK
line3603 = """"Many ages ago when I first left my country I explored these lands learning everything I could of alchemy. Back then I would harvest all my own ingredients. Now I supply up and coming alchemists and seasoned Adventurers."\n """
line3604 = """If you wish to purchase some of my ingredients I have a wide selection available. Just let me know if you are looking to BUY or if you need to SELL any, I can help with that too."\n """
line3605 = """Have you ever come across a Witch living alone in the woods? She and I were good friends back in our youth. She's a bit of an odd one, but quite knowledgeable in the ways of tonic making. Pay her a visit sometime."\n """
#37.Western Lake************************
line3701 = "You find yourself standing on the Western Lake beach. You watch as the waves gently stroke the shore while you plot out your course."
  #EXPLORE
line3702 = 'You take a look around the Lake and enjoy the peaceful scenery. Small fish can be spotted through the crystal clear water, as well as ducks floating across the surface. Across the way in the distance you can spot a Boat House. Saplings dot the field here, and a small and weathered path runs along the River leading SOUTH from here.\n'
#38. River - West Bank
line3801 = "You come to a small field on the western bank of the river. You can see the Forest across the water in the EAST.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line3802 = "Looking around you can see small trees dot the field around you, the river flowing rapidly NORTH towards the lake. One large pine tree stands near the center of the field. Below it looks to be a raft. EXAMINE for a closer look?\n"
line3803 = "Looking around you can see small trees dot the field around you, the river flowing rapidly NORTH towards the lake. One large pine tree stands near the center of the field. A raft sits on the edge of the river, ready to be taken across to the other side.\n"
line3804 = "Looking around you can see small trees dot the field around you, the river flowing rapidly NORTH towards the lake. One large pine tree stands near the center of the field. You can see a raft on the opposite side of the river. Too bad it's no use to you all the way over there.\n"
  #EXAMINE
line3805 = "You head over to the pine tree and take a look at the nearby raft. It looks to be in excellent condition despite being abandoned here. There's even an oar on top for you to use. Do you want to PUSH the raft over to the edge of the river, or LEAVE it alone?\n "
line3806 = "You take hold of the raft and begin pushing it to the edge of the river. After a little bit of elbow grease you manage to get the raft over and into position. Now you should have no trouble making it to the other side of the river! You can now SAIL across easily.\n"
line3807 = "The raft is already on the edge of the river. (Type SAIL to cross the river).\n"
line3808 = "The raft is on the opposite side of the river and cannot be used at this time."

#39. Fae Woods - Entrance***********************
line3901 = "You reach the entrance to the Fae Woods. The golden leaves of the trees glisten in the sun. Though beautiful, these woods are said to be treacherous."
  #EXPLORE
line3902 = "Children across the kingdom are told tales of the Fae Woods and the mythical beasts that lie beyond its borders. Despite the fantastic sights that may be seen within, a stark warning to stay away from the woods is always provided. Many mischievous creatures are said to inhabit the woods. You enter at your own peril."
  #ambush
line3903 = """As you travel SOUTH you approach a forest of golden leafed trees. As you get closer you can hear rustling coming from the tree tops. A crossbow bolt flies by your head, narrowly missing you. As you draw your weapon a group of rogues spring from the trees and surround you!\n\n"Not many travelers foolish enough to come 'round these parts! Not the brightest now are you, mate? I'll tell you what; we're feeling awfully generous. Drop all your gold and turn back, and we'll spare you... Or you can stay and we'll take everything off your corpse! Quickly, take your pick! Hahaha!"\n\nGIVE them your GP or FIGHT?"""
line3904 = """"What a coward! We should gut you just for being so yellow, but a pathetic wimp like you isn't worth the effort. Come on boys, let's head back to camp!"\n\nThe Rouges take their leave and disappear into the woods with all your GP. You really are a wuss.\n"""
line3905 = """"Going to make this fun for us I see? It's your funeral! HAHAHA! "\n"""
line3906 = "The Rouges are swiftly defeated after their failed ambush. Serves them right for their dastardly deeds. You find a purse of coins totalling 250 GP. Surely the original owners of this money would prefer you had it than those thugs.\n"

#40. Fae Woods - Camp
line4001 = "Through the Fae woods you enter a small clearing. Tucked away in the corner is a small campsite. A pair of tents sit and a log bench sit next to a firepit with a stack of tinder nearby. A perfect place to take a brief REST.\n"
line4002 = "Through the Fae woods you enter a small clearing. Tucked away in the corner is a small campsite. A pair of tents sit and a log bench sits next to a firepit. The nearby tinder has been all used up. A perfect place to take a quick break.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line4003 = "This appears to have been the camp of the Rouges that ambushed you earlier. Their supplies were running low so there wasn't much value left at the camp. There is still plenty of tinder to start a campfire and REST for a moment before you continue your journey. Surely the Rouges aren't going to mind...\n"
line4004 = "This appears to have been the camp of the Rouges that ambushed you earlier. Their supplies were running low so there wasn't much value left at the camp. The tinder has been all used up, but now that the Rouges are gone this is a nice safe spot to take a break while you plan your next course of action.\n"
  #Ambush
line4005 = """"Oi! What is this fool doing here? We thought you'd be running home with your tail between your legs by now. No matter. If you're desperate to be killed, we'll gladly oblige! Hahaha!"\n"""
line4006 = "The Rouges are swiftly defeated after their failed ambush. Serves them right for their dastardly deeds. You find a purse with all of your stolen money! At least you were able to get it all back, right?.\n"

#41. Crescent Pond
line4101 = 'Following the trail NORTH, you enter another clearing. A crescent shaped pond lies before you; you watch as fireflies dance above the water.'
  #EXPLORE
line4102 = "The trees here are tall and block out much of the light. Fireflies flicker above the water providing some additional illumination. You try to see the bottom of the pond but the water is much too dark. For some reason you have a strong urge to throw your weapon into the pond.\n"
line4103 = "The trees here are tall and block out much of the light. Fireflies flicker above the water providing some additional illumination. You try to see the bottom of the pond but the water is much too dark. You ponder where that strange woman went...\n"
line4104 = "The trees here are tall and block out much of the light. Fireflies flicker above the water providing some additional illumination. You try to see the bottom of the pond but the water is much too dark. You hope no more strange snake-women pop out of the water...\n"
  #SPECIAL
#line4105 = f"""You take your {p1.mainHand} and throw it into the pool. The water begins to foam and a woman clad in flowing white robes rises from the depths of the pond. In her hands she holds a blade of pure silver\n\n"Hello dear traveler. It seems you may have lost something in the waters... I have retrieved it for you. This is your SILVER SWORD, correct?\n" """
line4106 = """"Do not lie to me, filthy human. Your greedy kind does not belong here. Leave now!!!"\n\nThe woman emerges from the pool revealing her serpentine body! You prepare for combat with the Naga."""
line4107 = """"I see then... One moment."\n\nThe woman submerges herself back in the water and resurfaces a moment later, this time carrying a blade of pure gold.\n\n"This must be your GOLD SWORD then?"\n """
#line4108 = f"""The woman submerges herself in the pond once more this time pulling out the {p1.mainHand} you threw into the water.\n\n"This must be your weapon then. It does not befit one as noble as you thought. I will take this from you and in exchange I will grant you the ADAMANTITE SWORD. No blade is sharper or more durable. May it serve you well..."\n\n The woman pulls the ADAMANTITE SWORD from her robes and places the blade at your feet. You draw your new weapon and admire its immaculate craftsmanship before returning it to its scabbard. When you look back up the woman is already gone...\n """
#line4109 = f"""The defeated Naga writhes in agony on the ground before its gut burst open, the {p1.mainHand} falling to the ground. You wipe off the Naga's innards from the {p1.mainHand} and notice that it seems more polished than before."""

#42. Fae Woods - WEST
line4201 = "Moving through the forest you find yourself somewhere in the Fae Woods. A narrow path cuts through the trees from the EAST to the SOUTH.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line4202 = "As you move through these woods you feel as though you are being followed. It sounds like the trees themself are whispering and watching as you pass by them. The deeper you move through the woods, the less welcome you feel.\n"

#43. Fae Woods - SOUTH
line4301 = "You reach the SOUTH border of the Fae Woods. The expanse of golden trees is a wondrous sight to behold.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line4302 = "Despite the serene beauty of the woods, there are many sinister creatures that lurk beyond their borders. You remind yourself to stay cautious while in the home of the unpredictable Fae...\n"

#44. Mountain Pass**********************
line4401 = "You reach an intersection at the base of the great Drake Mountains and seek shade under a nearby tree to escape the scorching sun beating down on you.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line4402 = "You look around the intersection to see where each path leads. The path NORTH heads back up to the Fae Woods. In the EAST, the trail cuts through tree dotted hills where black smoke can be seen rising from the distance. In the SOUTH the passage up the Drake Mountains begins. Legends state that the highest peak is home to a great dragon of unimaginable power.\n"

#45. Dwarf Workshop
line4501 = "Following the smoke rising from over the rolling hills you come to a quaint cabin next to the workshop. A very short, but stout man with a beard as broad as his chest smokes a long pipe outside the home.\n"
line4502 = "Following the smoke rising from over the rolling hills you come to a quaint cabin next to the workshop. A proud dwarf with a beard as broad as his chest smokes a long pipe outside the home."
  #EXPLORE
line4503 = "The cabin tucked away in the hills is an impressively built, if not somewhat small home. The doors of the workshop are open and you can see various contraptions and creations you presume to be the invention of the man. You can also see various weapons and armor whose impressive quality can be seen, even from a distance. The man seems quite eager for you to request his services.\n"
line4504 = "The cabin tucked away in the hills is an impressively built, if not somewhat small home. The doors of the workshop are open and you can see various contraptions and creations you presume to be the invention of the dwarf. You can also see various weapons and armor whose impressive quality can be seen, even from a distance. The dwarf seems quite eager for you to request his services.\n"
  #SPEAK
line4505 = """"Finally someone haes come tae request mah services! Mah folk hae perfected th' art o' engineering 'n' mah knowledge is beyond that o' ony ither smith in th' lands; ye'll fin' na better craftsman in a' th' realm. Ah will be happy tae UPGRADE yer equipment or ah kin sell ye some personally crafted pieces if ye'r keekin tae BUY. If ye hae ony DRAGON SCALES ah will even TRADE ye yin o' mah masterpieces.\n ...Whit dae ah mean mah fowk? Cannae ye tell? A'm a damn dwarf!"\n """
line4506 = """"Come back tae request mah services! Mah folk hae perfected th' art o' engineering 'n' mah knowledge is beyond that o' ony ither smith in th' lands; ye'll fin' na better craftsman in a' th' realm. Ah will be happy tae UPGRADE yer equipment or ah kin sell ye some personally crafted pieces if ye'r keekin tae BUY. An' a', if ye hae ony DRAGON SCALES ah will TRADE ye yin o' mah masterpieces.\n """
line4506b = """"Come back tae request mah services! Mah folk hae perfected th' art o' engineering 'n' mah knowledge is beyond that o' ony ither smith in th' lands; ye'll fin' na better craftsman in a' th' realm. Ah will be happy tae UPGRADE yer equipment or ah kin sell ye some personally crafted pieces if ye'r keekin tae BUY.\n """
line4507 = """"Brought me something yi'll waant inspected? A'm na appraiser! Braw, braw! Ah will tak' a keek. Weel noo... It looks lik' ye'v stumbled onto something ferr amazing. This STREENGE GREASE 'ere is infact MAGIC GREASE. That enhances th' properties o' ony metal it coats. Pat it oan yer blades 'n' thay wull ne'er rust, nor wull thay dull. Ye hae enough 'ere tae lest twa lee times. If you'd be willing tae pairt wi' some a'd gladly gift ye yin one mah finest pieces?"\n"""
line4508 = """"Perfect! Let me see it. 'ere ye go; ah think this wull mak' fur a fair trade."\n """
line4509 = """"Damn grippie @$^*#!%! Come back if ye chaynge yer mynd then."\n """
line4510 = """"Changed yer mynd aboot offering some o` yer mae magic grease then?"\n """

  #Dwarf Village
line4511 = "You follow a narrow path leading away from the workshop and into a small village nestled in the hills. A collection of stout stone homes with thatched roofs sit among small gardens and farms. A few dwarfs can be seen going about their daily chores.\n"
line5412 = "This peaceful village tucked away in the mountain is a reminder of what these lands were once like before Smeldar's corruption spread across the kingdom. You take a moment to appreciate the simple beauty of the place before continuing on your journey.\n"

line5413 = """"Welcome tae oor humble village, stranger. We dinna git many visitors 'ere in the hills. If ye hae need o' eny supplies 'r services, ah suggest ye talk tae th' ol' SMITH at th' workshoppe."\n """
line5414 = """"If ye need tae res', ther's a inn NORTH of 'ere. Bed may be a wee smol fur sumone of yer size thoo..."\n"""

#46. Drake Mountains*********************
  #Drake Mountains 1
line4601 = "The beginning of the trail up the Mountain of Drakes lies before you. Looking up from the base, you can see the steep passage carving its way across the magnificent mountain range."
    #EXPLORE
line4602 = """In the distance are sharp peaks rising into the sky like the talons of a dragon. The uneven mountain pass ahead is bordered by craggy walls where lizards can be seen soaking in the heat emanating from the rocks. High up on the ridges you spot massive nests, the carcasses of various animals littering the ground below...\n\nCarved into the side of the mountain is an ancient petroglyph depicting a serpent with four wings carrying the sun in its mouth, raising from the EAST. Below the image are the characters "TA". This must have been left behind by the nearly forgotten dragon worshipers from ages past."""
  #Drake Mountains 2
line4603 = "You take great care on the mountain pass, being sure to hug the walls so as not to stumble and fall down the cliff face below. You take a moment to collect yourself once you come to a spot where the path widens."
    #EXPLORE
line4604 = """The sun is bright, but the air is cool high up in the mountains. Looking out from the cliff face Wyverns can be seen flying between the mountain peaks. The mountain walls are marred with deep claw marks; signs Wyverns have been sharpening their fierce talons nearby. Despite these cousins of dragons being far smaller, they are still terrifying sights to behold.\n\nOn the side of the pass stands a massive boulder with a weathered carving depicting the tail of a serpent with a crescent moon on its tip, flying across the sky. Below the image are the characters "IM". This must have been left behind by the nearly forgotten dragon worshipers from ages past."""
  #Drake Mountains 3
line4605 = "High up in the Mountain of Drakes you stand on a wide platform overlooking the valley. The clouds limit your view, otherwise you could probably see the entire kingdom from up here."
    #EXPLORE
line4606 = """The cold air chills your face and fingers up here near the mountain peaks. You can't see much over the cliff in the NORTH from the thick clouds concealing the land below. The screeching of Drakes echoes across the mountains... The mountain side to the SOUTH has a section made of an unusual dark stone unlike the rest of the rock that make up the mountains here.\n\nOn the mountain side near the dark stone wall a carving depicting a serpent with four wings carrying the sun in its mouth, lowering into WEST. Below the image are the characters "IN". This must have been left behind by the nearly forgotten dragon worshipers from ages past. """
line4607 = """The cold air chills your face and fingers up here near the mountain peaks. You can't see much over the cliff in the NORTH from the thick clouds concealing the land below. The screeching of Drakes echoes across the mountains...\n\nThe SOUTH mountain wall has disappeared and in its place lies a tunnel shrouded in mist..."""
line4607b = """The cold air chills your face and fingers up here near the mountain peaks. You can't see much over the cliff in the NORTH from the thick clouds concealing the land below. The screeching of Drakes echoes across the mountains...\n\nThe mist has cleared from the SOUTH tunnel leading up to the summit."""
  #SECRET
line4607c = """You speak the name "TANNINIM" in front of the dark rock wall facing SOUTH. Soon after the clouds above you begin to darken and swirl. You can feel the mountain begin to tremble, as if something has awoken deep within... Before your very eyes the wall begins to vanish, revealing a tunnel shrouded in mist."""
  #Drake Mountains 4
line4608 = "The winding mountain passage becomes precarious, necessitating careful movements across. You stop to check your surroundings to ensure the way forward is safe."
    #EXPLORE
line4609 = """The trail leaves little room for freedom as one side is flanked by the steep mountain side, the other by a deadly drop off a cliff's edge. You start to shiver as the mountain air cuts through your clothes.\n\nOn the mountain side near the dark stone wall a carving depicts a serpent with four wings carrying the sun in its mouth, flying high in the sky. Below the image are the characters "NN". This must have been left behind by the nearly forgotten dragon worshipers from ages past. """
#Drake Mountains 5
line4610 = "You come to a cliff edge and stare out into the distance. You can see across nearly the entire kingdom from here."
    #EXPLORE
line4611 = """On the very edge of the cliff stands a perfectly shaped obelisk carved from a single dark stone. Engraved on the front is a passage:\n\n"Time bewray the key\nSpeak its name at shadows door\nSeak the king and prove thy worth."\n """

#Drake Mountain Summit
line4612 = "After stepping through the misty tunnel you find yourself standing on the snowy summit of the Drake Mountains. The air is frigid and the sky filled with dark grey storm clouds."
line4613 = "You reach a snowy summit of the Drake Mountains. The air is frigid but the sky has started to clear."
    #EXPLORE
line4614 = "The sky has started to clear and the sun has started shining through the clouds. You can see all the lands SOUTH of the kingdom from this summit. If you fail on your quest it's certain Smeldar will turn his forces there next..."
  #AMBUSH
line4615 = """The sky is filled with dark swirling storm clouds. Lightning darts across the sky and thunder rumbles the mountains. Snow begins to whip through the air as the wind picks up.\n\nYou have a dreadful feeling about this place... You go to leave but before you have a chance to move you feel the mountain shake with such tremendous force you are knocked off your feet. While looking straight up into the sky you see it; four colossal dragon wings carrying a three headed dragon the size of a fortress making its way directly towards the summit. You quickly gather yourself just in time for the monumental serpent to land on the mountain, blocking any chance of escape. The dragon whips its forked tail back and forth as it unleashes an unholy screech that pierces the ears and chills sends a chill down your spine. You draw your weapon and prepare yourself for battle..."""
line4616 = """After delivering the fatal blow, the dragon's body ignites in bright green flames that consumes all its flesh and bones, until all that remains is its still beating heart. As you approach it, the heart begins to shrivel and harden into a crimson gem. You take the stone and place it in your bag, then you begin to rest.\n\nAfter taking a moment to gather yourself from a well-fought battle, you continue on your quest..."""

#47.Deep Woods******************** 
  #Deep Woods- Entrance
line4701 = "As you make your way through the woods the path begins to narrow and curve. You take a moment to get your bearings.\n"
    #EXPLORE
line4702 = 'You take a look around, but struggle to see through the dense forest. The narrow path sharply curves from the NORTH to the WEST. The wind blowing through the leaves sounds like whispers. You start to feel a chill.\n'
  #Deep Woods- SOUTH
line4703 = "The woods grow dark as you make your way through the Pinerift Forest. The surrounding woods are too dense to leave the path leading NORTH to SOUTH...\n"
    #EXPLORE
line4704 = 'The rustling of the leaves and branches coming deep within the woods keeps you on edge. At any moment it sounds as though a creature may leap out at you for an ambush. You make sure to stay on your guard as you make your way down the path...\n'
  #Deep Woods- Fork
line4705 = "The path widens a bit as you reach a fork in the road, deep within the Pinerift Forest. You stop for a moment to decide your next course of action. \n"
    #EXPLORE
line4706 = 'You stand in the middle of the fork and look around. The forked path runs from EAST to WEST, and back SOUTH. To the EAST, a dense mass of branches have fallen over and now block the way forward. EXAMINE for a closer look?\n'
line4707 = 'You stand in the middle of the fork and look around. The forked path runs from EAST to WEST, and back SOUTH. To the EAST, the mess of branches has been cleared away and the path forward is cleared.\n'
    #EXAMINE
line4708 = 'You walk up to the mess of dead branches lying on the path to the EAST. It does not look like there is an alternative way through. The branches look rather sturdy... If only you had a way to cut them away...\n'
line4709 = 'You walk up to the mess of dead branches lying on the path to the EAST. It does not look like there is an alternative way through. The branches look rather sturdy... Try to CUT them, or LEAVE them alone?\n'
line4710 = "You take your AXE and begin cutting away the dead branches. After a few moments you clear enough away to be able to make it through. Now the path to the EAST is clear!\n"
line4711 = "You attempt to cut away the dead branches, but your AXE is too dull and barely bites into the wood. You'll need a sharper AXE to clear these branches...\n"
line4711b = "You attempt to head east but are blocked by dead branches lying in the path. EXAMINE for a closer look?\n"
line4711c = "You look at the freshly cleared path; the way EAST is now open.\n"
line4711d = "You think about how much work it would be to clear away the branches and turn around. You've got better things to do than play with sticks.\n"
  #Deep Woods- WEST
line4712 = "You walk into a small clearing along the forest path; a lone bright patch in the middle of these dark woods. \n"
    #EXPLORE
line4713 = """The clearing here leaves enough space in the canopy for the sun's rays to reach the forest floor. You enjoy the warmth after walking through the dark and chilled forest. To the NORTH a group of saplings has overgrown the path, making the way forward inaccessible. You spot a tree with a message crudely carved quite low on the trunk. The message reads "Forest Shoppe located SOUTH; all forest folk welcome. NO HUMANS!"\n"""
line4714 = """The clearing here leaves enough space in the canopy for the sun's rays to reach the forest floor. You enjoy the warmth after walking through the dark and chilled forest. To the NORTH a group of saplings has been cleared from the path, making the way forward accessible. You spot a tree with a message crudely carved quite low on the trunk. The message reads "Forest Shoppe located SOUTH; all fairy folk welcome. NO HUMANS!"\n"""
    #EXAMINE
line4715 = "You approach the saplings and check for anyways. Unfortunately, the forest is too dense to go around and the saplings are too strong to try pushing through. You'll need a good AXE to clear the path.\n"
line4716 = "You approach the saplings and check for anyways. Unfortunately, the forest is too dense to go around and the saplings are too strong to try pushing through. You can try to CUT them away with your AXE, or leave them alone?\n"
line4717 = "You try to chop down the saplings, but your AXE is too dull and bounces off them. Maybe if your AXE was sharper you'd be able to make it through with ease.\n"
line4718 = "You grab your AXE and start hacking through the saplings. Before you know it the path is cleared! Now you can continue NORTH.\n"
line4718b = 'You attempt to travel NORTH, but the path is inaccessible; saplings have grown over the trail. EXAMINE for a closer look?\n'
line4718c = 'The saplings have been cleared away and the path NORTH has been made accessible once again.\n'
line4719 = 'You decide that whatever is on the other side of those saplings isn\'t worth the trouble of chopping them down and leaving them be.\n'
  #Deep Woods- Fallen Hive
line4720 = "You reach a giant hive at the base of an enormous pine tree. The hive appears to have taken a serious beating and been knocked over...\n"
  #EXPLORE
line4721 = "The forest smells like pollen and honey thanks to the massive hive lying on the ground. The hive ahead has been damaged heavily, but the entrance is accessible to the NORTH. Besides the rustling of leaves in the wind, it is quiet and there are no bees to be seen.\n"
  #Deep Woods- Forest Hut
line4722 = "Deep in the forest you come to a small hut tucked away between the trees. Outside, a strange blue creature with a rumpled face darts about nervously, muttering to itself frantically.\n"
line4723 = "Deep in the forest you come to a small hut tucked away between the trees. The Kobold Merchant seems to have calmed a bit, but he still looks nervous.\n"
line4724 = "Deep in the forest you come to a small hut tucked away between the trees. The Kobold Merchant is outside tidying up around its home with its 'friend'. They finally seem to trust you.\n"
    #EXPLORE
line4725 = "The hut between the trees is a strange building made from wood scraps and covered in moss. Out front is a small vegetable garden, although the plants look to be in a rather sorry state. The strange blue creature paces around with its head down, occasionally glancing at you making sure to keep its distance. It seems like it is looking for something.\n"
line4726 = "The hut between the trees is a strange building made from wood scraps and covered in moss. Out front is a small vegetable garden, although the plants look to be in a rather sorry state. The Kobold is still looking for his missing friend... Maybe you should help it SEARCH?\n"
line4727 = "The hut between the trees is a strange building made from wood scraps and covered in moss. Out front is a small vegetable garden, although the plants look to be in a rather sorry state. The Kobold has offered to sell you his wares now if you are looking to BUY.\n"
    #SPEAK
line4728 = """"Gets away! Its kind is nasty to Kobold. This Kobold wants peace. Eats its veggies, share its treasures with friend. Stay backs!"\n"""
line4729 = """"Evil humans be gone! Its come to harm us and I wont lets it! I'll protect friend... just where did friend go..."\n"""
line4730 = """"If its wonts leave then makes itself useful and help SEARCH for friend. He's disappeared! Brings him back, brings him back!"\n"""
line4731 = """"Its back again? If its don't has friend then go away! Go SEARCH for friend!"\n"""
line4732 = """"Its back again? Wait, whats its has? Thats not friend! Its tries to trick, but we Kobold are much too clever! Bring me friend for real!"\n"""
line4733 = """"Its back again? Wait, it has friend?! It has friend! Maybe its kind doesn't hate all Kobolds... Its can be my friend and we can share treasures! Yes, you give me shiny, shiny coins, and I will give you good things, helpful things!" (You can now BUY from the Kobold)\n"""
line4734 = """"Hello other friend! Come to bring the shiny coins? Me and friend have many good things to trade for!"\n """
    #SEARCH
line4735 = "You check behind a shrub and spy a snail sitting on a twig, chewing on a leaf. The snail has a smiley face painted on its shell. Could this be 'friend'?..\n"
line4736 = "You check around some trees and see a squirrel resting on a low branch. Could this be 'friend'?..\n"
line4737 = "You check out a small puddle near the garden. A toad is splashing around the water. Could this be 'friend'?..\n"
line4738 = "You can see 'friend' with the Kobold, resting on its shoulder and chomping down on a leaf."
  #Deep Woods- EAST
line4739 = "After walking through the woods for some time you come to another branching path. You look down the trail and decide on your next course of action.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line4740 = "From this point, the path branches off to the NORTH and EAST, deeper into the woods, and back WEST, towards the Shrine. The path NORTH shows signs of heavy travel, as if an army had marched through. A chill air blows from the EAST and eerie sounds can be heard coming from that direction. You feel as though you are being watched through the trees...\n"
  #Deep Woods- NORTH
line4741 = "The forest path begins to twist and wind through the trees obscuring the way forward...\n"
  #EXPLORE
line4742 = "The surrounding woods are dense and filled with thorny branches. Many of the trees look like they have started to decay; a sign of the WARLOCK Smeldar's influence taking hold. Large humanoid footprints seem to lead NORTH.\n"

#48. Tattered Hive
line4801 = "You step into the Tattered Hive. Honey drips from broken cells, and holes pockmark the hive's walls.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line4802 = "The hive has seen much better days judging by its dilapidated state. The holes in the walls look like they were chewed through from the outside. Corpses and severed bee limbs are spread all across the hive... It looks like a battle happened here recently; the attackers may still be nearby.  Most of the hive's cells have been broken apart and dripped with honey. A few intact cells remain, and appear to be sealed. Perhaps they have something inside worth trying to EXAMINE?\n"
line4803 = "The hive has seen much better days judging by its dilapidated state. The holes in the walls look like they were chewed through from the outside. Corpses and severed bee limbs are spread all across the hive... It looks like a battle happened here recently; let's hope that wasp was the only one hanging around... Most of the hive's cells have been broken apart and dripped with honey. A single intact cell remains sealed. Perhaps is has something inside worth trying to EXAMINE?\n"
line4804 = "The hive has seen much better days judging by its dilapidated state. The holes in the walls look like they were chewed through from the outside. Corpses and severed bee limbs are spread all across the hive... It looks like a battle happened here recently; let's hope that wasp was the only one hanging around... Most of the hive's cells have been broken apart and dripped with honey. The last of the cells have already been opened and searched.\n"
  #EXAMINE
line4805 = "You go to approach the intact cells when suddenly a wriggling mass bursts from one! A massive Larva squirms its way out of the cell. The newborn insect immediately turns towards you and rushes forward. The creature opens its maw and attempts to make you its first meal! You jump back and draw your weapon, preparing for battle!\n"
line4806 = "The Larva draws the last breath of its short life, but before you have time to rejoice, you hear a buzzing rapidly approaching. Your troubles are far from over; you look up and watch a Giant Wasp crawl through one of the holes in the side of the hive. The Giant Wasp instantly turns its sights on you, charging flying forward like a missile! You manage to parry the flying pests spear-like stinger, evading its first attack. You ready yourself for combat once again!\n"
line4807 = "The Giant Wasp is crushed, and you are finally able to relax for a moment. You help yourself to some of the honey dripping from the broken cells to regain some energy. Almost as sweet as your victory!\n"
line4808 = "You go back to search the remaining intact cell. After removing the wax and unsealing the cell you find it contains ROYAL JELLY! This jelly has an unusually deep red color. You take a large vial and fill it with the STRANGE JELLY.\n"
line4809 = "You've already searched everything of interest here.\n"

#49. Orc Fortress*****************************
  #Outer Fortress
line4901 = "At the NORTH border of the Pinerift Forest you come to the entrance of a walled fortress. Guard towers flank either side of the entrance through the palisade walls.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line4902 = "The fortress ahead is surrounded by a palisade wall. The thick trunks used to form the wall combined with a series of guard towers make for a formidable defensive structure. Several guards can be seen patrolling outside the fort and a pair stands in each tower. The residents of the fortress are no humans however; their green skin and tusks reveal this to be an Orc military base.\n"
  #Orc Fort 1
line4903 = "You reach the Orc Fort's entrance and take cover by some stacked supplies. You look toward the small keep to the NORTH of the camp.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line4904 = "Across the Fort's entrance are various supply crates filled with army provisions and equipment. Orcs are masters of warfare and fiercely logistical. To the NORTH a small keep stands before you; the entrance blocked by a heavy portcullis. Outside the gate stand two mechanisms; they look like they are missing parts...\n"
line4905 = "Across the Fort's entrance are various supply crates filled with army provisions and equipment. Orcs are masters of warfare and fiercely logistical. To the NORTH a small keep stands before you; the entrance blocked by a heavy portcullis. Outside the gate stand two mechanisms; One CRANK doesn't seem to be enough to open the gate. Looks like you'll need to repair both mechanisms to enter the keep.\n"
line4906 = "To the NORTH a small keep stands before you; the gate has been lifted and the way forward is clear.\n"
  #EXAMINE
line4907 = "You approach the mechanisms flanking the gate ahead. Thick iron chains run from the mechanisms into the wall above the portcullis. There doesn't appear to be any way to lift the gate, however. Both mechanisms seem to be missing a part; each has a circular slot that would appear to fit a crank... Maybe if you find the missing parts you can fix the mechanism and open the path?\n"
line4908 = "You approach the mechanisms flanking the gate ahead. Thick iron chains run from the mechanisms into the wall above the portcullis. The gate still will not budge after repairing the first mechanism. It looks like both will need to be repaired to get through...\n"
line4909 = "You approach the mechanisms flanking the gate ahead. Thick iron chains run from the mechanisms into the wall above the portcullis. The gate has been lifted and the path ahead has been cleared... Are you prepared for what may lie inside the Orc's Keep?\n"
line4910 = "You approach the mechanisms flanking the gate ahead. Thick iron chains run from the mechanisms into the wall above the portcullis. There doesn't appear to be any way to lift the gate, however. Both mechanisms seem to be missing a part; each has a circular slot that would appear to fit a crank... Would you like to try to INSERT one of the CRANKS, or LEAVE the mechanisms alone for now?\n"
line4911 = "You approach the mechanisms flanking the gate ahead. Thick iron chains run from the mechanisms into the wall above the portcullis. The gate still will not budge after repairing the first mechanism. Would you like to try to INSERT the other CRANK, or LEAVE the mechanism alone for now?\n"
line4912 = "You insert a CRANK into one of the mechanism's slots. The gate barely moves when you try to turn the CRANK. It looks like the chain from the other mechanism is getting stuck without another CRANK inserted. Looks like you'll need to fix the other side to enter the keep.\n"
line4913 = "You insert a CRANK into the other mechanism's slot. You start to slowly turn the CRANK, and the gate begins to rise! The entrance to the Orc's Keep has been cleared."
line4914 = "Before you are able to celebrate, a group of Orcs take notice and charge forward to apprehend you!\n"
line4915 = "Surprisingly, none of the Orcs notice you opening the gate. You quietly celebrate your success!\n"
line4916 = "You decide against fixing the mechanism for now. Really, is it you job to make repairs to the Orc's infrastructure anyway?\n"
line4917 = "You attempt to enter the Orc Keep but a massive gate stands in your way. A pair of mechanisms stand on either side of the gate. EXAMINE them for a closer look?\n"
  #Orc Fort 2
line4918 = "You move through the Orc Fortress and come to a group of tents. It looks like this is where the Orc forces are quartered.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line4919 = "Rows of tents and stacks of military equipment fill this section of the fort. A few Orcs can be seen lying on damp straw piles inside their tents asleep. No wonder Orcs always smell like moldy socks... Next to one of the tents you spy a wood chest. Perhaps you should SEARCH it?\n"
line4919b = "Rows of tents and stacks of military equipment fill this section of the fort. A few Orcs can be seen lying on damp straw piles inside their tents asleep. No wonder Orcs always smell like moldy socks. An open chest sits next to one of the tents. That's where you found the CRANK, remember?\n"
  #EXAMINE
line4920 = "You take a look at the wood chest next to the tents. Unfortunately the chest looks like it's locked. You could try to SMASH the lock, or SEARCH for the key? Maybe you should just LEAVE it alone...\n"
line4921 = "You decide it's not worth the trouble to find a dumb key and opt for a more direct approach; you take hold of your weapon and start swinging wildly at the lock. Eventually, the lock breaks and the chest pops open. Before you have a chance to check inside, an Orc approaches you with an angry look. It would seem he doesn't appreciate you waking him from his nap and rummaging through his things..."
line4922 = "You decide it would be best to leave the chest alone for now..."
line4923 = "You take a look at the wood chest next to the tents. Unfortunately the chest looks like it's locked. You can try to OPEN it with the key you found, SMASH the lock, or LEAVE it alone for now?\n"
line4924 = "You insert the CHEST KEY and it successfully opens the box! You search inside for any spoils and find a CRANK. Looks like this was removed from a mechanism for some strange reason.\n"
line4925 = "You decide why try some dumb key when you can go for a more direct approach; you take hold of your weapon and start swinging wildly at the lock. Eventually, the lock breaks and the chest pops open. Before you have a chance to check inside, an Orc approaches you with an angry look. It would seem he doesn't appreciate you waking him from his nap and rummaging through his things..."
line4926 = "You turn away from the chest and leave it for now. Who even likes treasure anyway? Psh.\n"
line4926b = "The chest is empty now; why are you wasting time looking in here?\n"
  #SEARCH
line4927 = "You take a look around the area to see if you can find a key to the chest. You spot one Orc sleeping in their tent with a key tied to their belt. Should you try to STEAL the key, or LEAVE and look for another?\n"
line4928 = "You slowly approach the sleeping Orc, taking care not to make any noise. You manage to untie the keyring from the Orcs belt. No sooner does the Orc begin to move around...\n"
line4929 = "The Orc begins to roll over in his pile of hay, softly grumbles, then falls back to sleep. You quickly sneak off and get away with the key safely.\n"
line4930 = "The Orc sits up and rubs his eyes. After a couple seconds he sees you standing right over him, clutching the key. The Orc kicks you back, jumps up and draws his weapon. Looks like he isn't going to make this easy for you...\n"
line4931 = "You determine it's not worth the risk and leave the Orc to his nap.\n"
  #Orc Fort 3
line4932 = "You pass by a guard tower and enter a training ground.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line4933 = "Training dummies and archery targets line the perimeter of the training ground. Bundles of arrows and piles of weapons can be found on tables and stands scattered across the field. A few Orcs can be seen practicing archery and some other patrolling; you try to stay out of view as you make your way through the area.\n"
line4934 = "Training dummies and archery targets line the perimeter of the training ground. Bundles of arrows and piles of weapons can be found on tables and stands scattered across the field. The Orcs seem to have mostly fled after the defeat of their captain. Still, you try to stay hidden in case of any stragglers...\n"
  #Orc Fort 4
line4935 = "Deeper into the fort you come to a massive war tent and stockpile of provisions. You take cover by a stack of boxes.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line4936 = "An impressive, blood red war tent stands by the palisade wall. To the right stands a guard tower with orcs watching the outer perimeter of the fort. Between the tent and the tower is an unopened chest. With all the orcs patrolling the area it may be risky trying to open it...\n"
line4937 = "An impressive, blood red war tent stands by the palisade wall. To the right stands a guard tower with orcs watching the outer perimeter of the fort. Between the tent and the tower is an unopened chest. With all the orcs drawn away from this area it may be the perfect time to try to open it.\n"
line4938 = "An impressive, blood red war tent stands by the palisade wall. To the right stands a guard tower with orcs watching the outer perimeter of the fort. Between the tent and the tower is an opened chest where you found a CRANK. It doesn't look like there's anything else around here worth checking out.\n"
  #EXAMINE
line4939 = "You look over to the chest between the war tent and the guard tower. Orcs have been patrolling the area between you and the chest regularly... Do you want to SNEAK over to the chest, or LEAVE it alone?\n"
line4940 = "While sneaking over to the chest a patrolling orc spots you! The orc draws its weapon and rushes you!\n"
line4941 = "You see far fewer orcs patrolling the area now and quickly sneak over to the chest between the war tent and the guard tower.\n"
line4942 = "You defeat the orc and hurry over to the chest before anyone else can spot you. You go to open it, but find that the hinges have rusted and the top will not budge. Nearby there is a metal rod you may be able to use to PRY open the box, or you could always just SMASH it. (Or you can LEAVE it alone for now.)\n"
line4943 = "You successfully sneak over to the chest. You go to open it, but find that the hinges have rusted and the top will not budge. Nearby there is a metal rod you may be able to use to PRY open the box, or you could always just SMASH it. (Or you can LEAVE it alone for now.)\n"
line4944 = "You grab the rod and begin trying to pry open the chest.\n"
line4945 = "The rod slips and you fail to open the chest. While you are attempting to open it, a patrolling orc catches you and attacks!\n"
line4946 = "The rod slips and you fail to open the chest. Luckily no one spotted you. Do you attempt to PRY open the chest again or SMASH it? (Or you can LEAVE it alone for now.)\n"
line4947 = "You manage to defeat the orc. It doesn't look like anyone else has spotted you. Do you attempt to PRY open the chest again or SMASH it? (Or you can LEAVE it alone for now.)\n"
line4948 = "You jam the rod in between the container and the lid and force it open with all your might. The lid pops open and the contents reveal themself! You find a CRANK in the chest and put it in your pack. Surely this will come in handy later.\n"
line4949 = "You take the more direct route and simply smash the chest with the nearby metal rod. The lid falls to pieces following a loud crash. You take a look inside and discover a CRANK. You place it in your pack; surely this will come in handy later.\n\nBefore you have time to leave a shadowy figure appears in the entrance of the war tent. A massive orc clad in heavy armor steps forth and stares you down. Smashing the chest must have alerted the Orc Commander to your presence here... You draw your weapon and begin to fight the orc!\n"
line4949b = "The Orc Commander proved to be no match for you. After his defeat you waste no time in returning to cover before any other Orcs discover you.\n"
line4950 = "You decide to leave the chest alone for now and move back to your hiding spot by the crates.\n"
  #Orc Fort 5
line4951 = "You enter the back of the Orc Fort and take cover under a pile of equipment in the center of the area. Nothing in the pile would be very useful on your journey; except as cover right now.\n"  
  #EXPLORE
line4952 = "You take a look around and see Orcs passing by; luckily none notice you in your hiding spot. On the NORTH wall you can see a carefully stacked pile of wood and a nearby torch; it looks to be set up as a signal fire to alert the orcs of an incoming attack from the NORTH... On the same wall you spot a wooden chest. It doesn't appear to have been opened yet.\n"
line4953 = "You take a look around and see Orcs passing by; luckily none notice you in your hiding spot. On the NORTH wall you can see the signal fire you lit, drawing away some of the orc forces from the fort... On the same wall you spot a wooden chest. It doesn't appear to have been opened yet.\n"
line4954 = "You take a look around and see Orcs passing by; luckily none notice you in your hiding spot. On the NORTH wall you can see a carefully stacked pile of wood and a nearby torch; it looks to be set up as a signal fire to alert the orcs of an incoming attack from the NORTH... On the same wall you spot a wooden chest. It's the same one you've already opened it though.\n"
line4955 = "You take a look around and see Orcs passing by; luckily none notice you in your hiding spot. On the NORTH wall you can see the signal fire you lit, drawing away some of the orc forces from the fort... On the same wall you spot a wooden chest. It's the same one you've already opened it though.\n"
  #EXAMINE
line4956 = "You take a look towards the NORTH wall. To your right you see a large wooden chest, and to your left a pile of wood and torch. Do you want to check out the CHEST or the WOOD pile? (Or type BACK to leave them alone.)\n"
line4957 = "You take a look towards the NORTH wall. To your right you see a large wooden chest. Do you want to check out the CHEST? (Or type BACK to leave it alone.)\n"
line4958 = "You take a look towards the NORTH wall. To your left you see a pile of wood and torch. Do you want to check out the WOOD pile? (Or type BACK to leave it alone.)\n"
line4959 = "You slowly approach the chest, taking care not to be caught by any patrolling orcs. The chest appears to be shut tight, but there is no lock. A prime target for looting. OPEN, SMASH, or LEAVE it alone?\n"
line4960 = "You carefully open the chest and look inside. As you open the lid you hear a click. Soon after a noxious gas is expelled from the container. The gas fills your lungs, burning your throat.\n"
line4960b = "After a few minutes of coughing blood you can finally breathe again. You take a look inside the chest to find a few potions. Neat! You grab what you can carry and quickly return to cover.\n"
line4961 = "You throw caution to the wind and smash the chest open! Unfortunately, you also smashed the contents to pieces. Good going. Maybe next time you'll be more careful?\n"
line4962 = "You throw caution to the wind and smash the chest open! You take a look inside the chest to find a few potions. Luckily they didn't get crushed! You grab what you can carry and quickly return to cover.\n"
line4963 = 'You change your mind about the chest and head back to cover. Is loot really worth risking your life over?\n'
line4964 = "You crawl over to the pile of wood and safely make it over. You've heard of armies using fires to signal incoming invasions... maybe lighting this pile will draw some orcs away from the fort. Do you want to try to LIGHT a signal fire, or LEAVE it alone?\n"
line4965 = "You grab the nearby torch and throw it onto the pile. The wood ignites quickly, and a plume of smoke soon becomes visible. You rush back to take cover before you can be discovered by the orcs. You observe several groups of orcs marching towards the exit to the fort... It looks like your plan was a success! There should be fewer patrolling orcs to worry about now...\n"
line4966 = "You grab the nearby torch and throw it onto the pile. The wood ignites quickly, and a plume of smoke soon becomes visible. Before you can make it back to cover, you are discovered by the orcs! A pair of orcs rush you!\n"
line4967 = "Both Orcs have been defeated, but it would appear your plan to draw the orcs away has failed... Looks like they are even more alert to your presence here now.\n"
line4968 = "You think about lighting the wood pile for a moment but wuss out and head back to cover. It's okay, no one can see how embarrassed you are."
line4969 = "It's a bit too risky for that now, you think to yourself. You decide to stay where you are until you come up with a better course of action.\n "
line4970 = "On the NORTH wall, the signal fire has been lit and the chest has been opened. You've thoroughly cleared out this section of the fort it would seem.\n "
  #Orc Keep
line4971 = "You stand in the middle of the Orc King's keep. The keep has been left deserted after the Orc King's defeat.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line4972 = "The keep is vast and empty. Bones picked clean of meat from a mix of various creatures- man and beast alike, are scattered across the floor. Near the center of the room lies a pile of weapons, seemingly lumped into the shape of a throne. It's hard to imagine anyone trying to sit on that, but Orcs aren't known for appreciating comfort.\n"
  #EXAMINE
line4973 = "write something about the tapestries here. IDFK is not that important. PLACEHOLDER TEXT"
  #ambush
line4974 = """You step past the portcullis and enter the Orc Keep. You walk down a long, dark hall, pressing your hands against the cold stone walls to help keep your footing. After a moment you enter the dimly lit great hall. In the back of the room, a figure concealed by shadows sits on a large metal throne. Slowly the figure begins to stand and step forward into the light.\n"Foolish human, how bold of you to enter my fortress. My master has been watching your every move. Your arrival has been anticipated. I, Orc King Kargath will deliver your bloody skull on a pike to Smeldar!"\n """  
line4975 = "After an intense battle the king of the Orcs is slayed. You examine his remains and find a key on a chain around his neck. You yank the key off and examine it. It is another WARLOCK KEY! You place the ORC'S WARLOCK KEY in your inventory. Your quest is one step closer to the end. Soon enough you will face the wicked Smeldar...\n"

#50. Misty Woods*************************
  #Woods NORTH
line5001 = "You continue through the forest until you come to a bend in the path. A faint mist fills the space between the trees.\n"
      #EXPLORE
line5002 = "A cold breeze passes through the trees sending a chill down your back. Strange sounds and rustling of leaves can be heard coming deeper from the woods. A thick fog can be seen filling the space between the trees in the distance, concealing anything hiding within the woods.\n"
line5003 = "A cold breeze passes through the trees sending a chill down your back. Strange sounds and rustling of leaves can be heard coming deeper from the woods; the mist conceals anything hiding in the forest, however.\nThe bone fragments scattered around are gone. Hopefully that was the last Necromancer you come across...\n"
      #EXAMINE
line5004 = "You take a closer look at the bone fragments scattered across the ground. You notice some of the bones show signs of scorching... as if they had been burned in some ritual. You've heard rumors before of Necromancers conducting dark rituals in these woods. It would be best to proceed through this area with caution...\n"
  #Woods Central
line5005 = "You continue through the forest. The mist has grown into a thick fog, concealing the woods and the path ahead...\n"
line5005b = "You continue through the forest. The mist has grown into a thick fog, concealing the woods. The fog blocking the path forward has dissipated, clearing the way forward.\n"
      #EXPLORE
line5006 = "The path ahead is blocked by a thick fog. You can't see anything but the trees and the path behind you. You'll need to find a way to deal with this fog if you want to continue SOUTH... Just off the main path to the WEST you can make out a narrow trail continuing through the woods.\n"
line5007 = "The thick fog has been cleared from the path ahead thanks to the DIVINE FLAME LANTERN! Now you can travel SOUTH from here. Just off the main path to the WEST you can make out a narrow trail continuing through the woods.\n"
  #Woods Camp
line5008 = "At the end of the side trail you reach an old camp site. A well constructed fire pit lined with soot covered stones sits at the center of the camp. You take a seat on a fallen tree trunk by the pit and take a break on your long journey.\n"
      #EXPLORE
line5009 = "You sit on the fallen tree trunk and look at the fire pit. A pile of ash sits in the center. Just off to the side a pile of tinder waits to be used to start a new fire. Seems like there's enough here to REST at least a few times. It might be wise considering there aren't many other safe locations in the forest remaining...\n"
line5010 = "You sit on the fallen tree trunk and look at the fire pit. A pile of ash sits in the center. No more tinder remains to start a new fire. It's time to continue on your quest.\n"
  # Woods South
line5011 = "You continue through the woods, passing through the now thin fog. The narrow path leaves little room to travel down.\n"
      #EXPLORE
line5012 = "Between the densely packed trees and the fog still lingering in the air you struggle to see much outside the forest trail. In the distance you can hear the howling of wolves...\n"
  # Woods East
line5013 = "The forest path begins to darken and starts to wind through the trees. Without your lantern you'd be bumping into trees left and right.\n"
      #EXPLORE
line5014 = "You take notice that this part of the woods is much darker than it should be at this time of the day. You try to look around but it has become as dark as night. The light from your lantern carries down the trail, but is unable to penetrate the densely packed trees surrounding you. You sense something sinister nearby...\n"

#51. Vampire Castle*********************
    #Outer
line5101 = "You stand at the entrance of a massive stone palace. The sky above is dark and cloudy, with only faint moonlight breaking through the gloom. An eerie silence fills the air around you.\n"
line5102 = "The cold earth beneath your feet is damp and uneven. The sound of crows cawing in the nearby trees fills the air. You feel a dark presence drawing you into the palace...\n"
    #Palace 1
line5103 = "You stand at the entrance of the enormous palace. Large reliefs of the moon adorn the stone walls. The palace seems to absorb the faint moonlight, giving it an ominous appearance.\n"
line5103b = "You stand at the entrance of the enormous palace. Large reliefs of the moon adorn the stone walls. Intense moonlight spills into the foyer from the WEST hall, illuminating the room.\n"
line5104 = "Your every movement echoes though the massive room as you move throughout the palace foyer. The air is cold and stale; a chill runs down your spine as you take in your surroundings.\n"
line5104b = "Your every movement echoes though the massive room as you move throughout the palace foyer. The moonlight shining through the WEST hall is intense, brightening the space around you.\n"
   #Palace 2
line5105 = "Your steps echo across the marble floor as you enter a grand hall. You stand at a four-way intersection leading deeper into the palace.\n"
line5106 = "Paintings depicting various night scenes and bloodied soldiers hang on the walls. The flickering light from the hanging sconces gives the illusion that the battling knights are actually moving.\n"
    #Palace 3
line5107 = "You enter a poorly lit hall. Suits of armor and paintings decorate the walls as you walk though a wide open hall. A deep, blood-red rug extends down the hall muting your steps along the cold stone floor.\n"
line5107b = "You enter a hall illuminated by moonlight. Suits of armor and paintings decorate the walls as you walk though a wide open hall. A deep, blood-red rug extends down the hall muting your steps along the cold stone floor.\n"
line5108 = "Suits of armor stand at attention along the end of the hall. Between them hang golden framed portraits of a man and woman. It's hard to make out their features in the dim light, but you can see their fine clothing and regal postures.\n"
line5108b = "Suits of armor stand at attention along the end of the hall. Between them hang golden framed portraits of a man and woman. Their faces now clearly visible in the moonlight, you can see their monstrous features; their gaunt faces and fanged mouths hardly resembling anything human.\nYou can hear the quiet snarls of a beast lurking somewhere...\n"
line5108c = "You look around the hall sensing something is off. You can't help shake the feeling that you are being watched. Suddenly you hear the snarls of a wolf coming from the armory...\n You have just enough time to ready yourself for combat before a Werewolf charges you from the shadows!\n"
line5108d = "After defeating the Werewolf you take a moment to catch your breath. The hall is now eerily silent once again.\n"
line5108e = "You see something unusual stinking out of the Werewolf's mouth. Against your better judgement you stick your hand in and grab it. It's a SAPPHIRE GEMSTONE of extreme quality! You place the SAPPHIRE GEMSTONE in your inventory; hopefully it will be of some use later.\n"
line5108f = "Suits of armor stand at attention along the end of the hall. Between them hang golden framed portraits of a man and woman. Their faces now clearly visible in the moonlight, you can see their monstrous features; their gaunt faces and fanged mouths hardly resembling anything human.\nThe hall is now eerily silent once again.\n"
line5108g = "Hopefully there aren't any more Werewolves lurking in the palace... Probably shouldn't stick around to find out.\n"
    #Palace 4
line5109 = "You enter a dusty armory. A single flickering scone lights the room. Cobwebs and racks of old weapons and armor fill the space.  A full suit of armor propped in the corner; in the dim light you could swear it was watching you. A lever in the middle of the floor catches your eye.\n"
line5109b = "You enter a dusty armory. A single flickering scone lights the room. Cobwebs and racks of old weapons and armor fill the space. The broken pieces of the Living Armor lie scattered on the floor. The lever in this room has already been activated; probably best not to mess with it.\n"
line5110 = "All this equipment looks old and unusable; too bad monsters aren't weak to rust and rotted wood. The lever in the center of the room looks functional though; it appears to be connected to a series of chains running along the ceiling. Maybe pulling the lever will open a door somewhere in the palace?\n" 
line5110b = "All this equipment looks old and unusable; too bad monsters aren't weak to rust and rotted wood. The lever here has already been activated. No sense pulling it again.\n"
line5111 = "You slowly approach the lever trying not to stumble over the mess of rusted equipment. Pull the lever? YES or NO?\n"
line5111b = "Without hesitation you pull back the lever. Before you can continue pulling the lever you feel a sharp pain in your shoulder as a lance pierces your flesh. The armor in the corner of the room has sprung to life and readies another attack!\n"
line5111c = "You cautiously back away from the lever, your senses telling you something is awry. You turn to look behind you and in that instant manage to narrowly avoid an incoming thrust from a Living Armor! You ready yourself for combat!\n"
line5111d = "After defeating the Living Armor you reapproach the lever and pull it back. The sound of moving gears can be heard echoing through the halls in the distance.\n"
line5111e = "After defeating the Living Armor you reapproach the lever and pull it back. The sound of moving gears and the rumbling of large doors opening can be heard echoing through the halls coming from a distant room.\n"
    #Palace 5
line5112 = "Continuing down the hall you reach a bend in the corridor. A sturdy iron gate halts your progress through the passageway.\n"
line5112b = "Continuing down the hall you reach a bend in the corridor. The iron gate has slid open, opening up the rest of the path.\n"
line5113 = "The corridor is decorated with statues depicting Dark Knights. The iron gate blocking the western passage is locked tight, and you can see no obvious way to open it.\n"
line5113b = "The corridor is decorated with statues depicting Dark Knights. The iron gate is no longer blocking the western passage. It would seem the Vampire Queen's dark magic has been dispelled.\n"
line5114 = "You approach the iron gate and attempt to pull it open, but it doesn't budge. It seems to be magically sealed. You'll need to find a way to break the seal if you wish to progress further into the palace...\n"
line5114b = "You attempt to open the gate, but you realize they're already open. Are you even paying attention?\n"
    #Palace 6
line5115 = "You enter a dimly lit chamber. The air is thick with dust and the faint smell of decay.\n"
line5116 = "Old tapestries hang limply from the walls, their once vibrant colors now faded and dull. The NORTH wall is ornately decorated with carvings of twisted vines and grotesque faces and a locked door. The lock is unlike any you've seen before with a fascinatingly complex mechanism. Perhaps you could find a way to unlock it elsewhere in the palace...\n"
line5116b = "Old tapestries hang limply from the walls, their once vibrant colors now faded and dull. The NORTH wall is ornately decorated with carvings of twisted vines and grotesque faces and a locked door. The lock is unlike any you've seen before with a fascinatingly complex mechanism. It would appear pulling that lever caused some of the parts to shift... Perhaps there is another lever nearby?\n"
line5116c = "Old tapestries hang limply from the walls, their once vibrant colors now faded and dull. The NORTH wall is ornately decorated with carvings of twisted vines and grotesque faces. The door has been unlocked and has lifted itself, opening up the way forward.\n"
line5116d = "You take a closer look at the intricate lock on the NORTH door. The mechanism appears to be made up of several interlocking gears and cogs. There is no way you are getting through this door without finding the mechanism to unlock it.\n"
line5116e = "You take a closer look at the intricate lock on the NORTH door. The mechanism appears to be made up of several interlocking gears and cogs. It looks like pulling a lever somewhere in the palace may have shifted some of the parts into place. Perhaps there is another lever nearby that you can pull to fully unlock the door?\n"
line5116f = "The door has been unlocked and has lifted itself, opening up the way forward. Time to move on...\n"
    #Palace 7
line5117 = "You step into a dirty cluttered room filled with broken furniture and tattered clothes. It would appear this was once a servant's quarters.\n"
line5118 = "The room smells musty and stale. Every surface appears covered in either dust or mold. Amidst the clutter you spot a lever protruding from the wall.\n"
line5118b = "The room smells musty and stale. Every surface appears covered in either dust or mold. The wall lever has already been activated. No use trying to pull it again.\n"
line5118c = "The room smells musty and stale. Every surface appears covered in either dust or mold. The wall the Flesh Golem busted through has partially collapsed, with debris blocking up the hole. The wall lever has already been activated. No use trying to pull it again.\n"
line5119 = "You approach the lever protruding from the wall. It looks badly rusted but still functional; pulling it may open something in the palace.\n"
line5119b = "You remember the MAGIC GREASE you found earlier. It might help with the rust. Try applying it to the lever? (YES or NO)\n"
line5119c = "You apply the MAGIC GREASE to the lever, that should make it much easier to pull.\n"
line5119d = "You decide against applying the grease. Hopefully you can manage to pull the lever without it.\n"
line5119e = "Pull the lever now? (YES or NO)\n"
line5120 = "You pull back the lever. The sound of moving gears can be heard coming from the previous room.\n"
line5120b = "You pull back the lever. The sound of moving gears and a large door opening can be heard coming from the previous room.\n"
line5120c = "You grip the rusted lever and try pulling back with all your might. After a few strenuous tugs the lever finally starts to give way with a loud creak. Before you can finish pulling the lever a Flesh Golem bursts through the WEST wall and hits you with a piece of rubble! \n"
line5120d = "You manage to down the Flesh Golem and return to your task.\n"
line5120e = "You successfully pull back the lever. The sound of moving gears can be heard coming from the previous room.\n"
    #Palace Dungeon
line5121 = "You enter a dark, damp dungeon. The air is thick with the smell of mold and decay. You can make out faint moans echoing through the dark cells, as though vengeful spirits haunt the place.\n"
line5122 = "The dungeon is filled with rows of cells lining the walls. Most of the cells are empty, but a few contain human remains chained to the walls or strewn about the floor. The dungeon is far from functional these days, as many of the bars have rusted through revealing gaps that could be exploited and slipped through.\n"
line5122b = "The dungeon is filled with rows of cells lining the walls. Most of the cells are empty, but a few contain human remains chained to the walls. The dungeon is far from functional these days, as many of the bars have rusted through revealing gaps that could be exploited and slipped through. A large section of wall in one of the EAST cells has collapsed in. This must be where the Flesh GOlem was being kept...\n"
    #Queen's Chamber
line5123 = "You step into a lavishly decorated chamber. Gold and precious gems decorate the walls and furniture. A large wardrobe and vanity sit against the wall, and a beautifully and masterfully carved coffin lies in the center of the room.\n"
line5124 = "Every inch of the room is adorned with intricate patterns and designs, showcasing the wealth and power of its occupant. Despite the opulence, the room is saturated in the smell of blood. You sense an evil presence coming from the coffin at the center of the room...\n"
line5124b = "Every inch of the room is adorned with intricate patterns and designs, showcasing the wealth and power of its occupant. Despite the opulence, the room is saturated in the smell of blood. The Vampire Queen's ashes lie defeated beside her coffin, her dark magic dispelled.\n"
line5125 = "You cautiously approach the coffin at the center of the room. The lid is sealed shut, but you can feel a dark energy emanating from within.\n"
line5125b = """As you reach for the lid of the coffin, it slowly creaks open. A chilling wind fills the room as the Vampire Queen rises from her resting place. "Foolish mortal, you dare to enter my chamber and disturb my slumber? You shall pay with your life!"\n"""
line5125c = "With a final, anguished wail, the Vampire Queen's form dissipates into a cloud of ash. Immediately you sense the Queen's Dark energy has been dispelled! In the distance the rumbling of a gate can be heard...\n"
    #Palace 8
line5126 = "You stand at the end of a long corridor. The walls are lined with more faded portraits of long-dead nobles and aged statues.\n"
line5127 = "As you stand in the corridor you begin to wonder what secrets this place holds. For starters, how many statues did the owner of this place have to buy to fill it out?\n"
    #Palace 9
line5128 = "You enter a massive intersection deep within the Forest Palace. You take a moment to look around the grand hall while you decide your next steps. \n"
line5129 = "The room's high ceiling is supported by ornate columns, the floor is covered in a rich red carpet, and the walls are adorned with tapestries depicting scenes of battle and victory. Shadows appear to creep across the walls. To the NORTH, you see a large set of double doors, while to the EAST and WEST are smaller doorways. The NORTH doors seem to repel you as you try to approach them, as if some dark force is keeping you at bay.\n"
line5129b = "The room's high ceiling is supported by ornate columns, the floor is covered in a rich red carpet, and the walls are adorned with tapestries depicting scenes of battle and victory. Shadows appear to creep across the walls. To the NORTH, you see a large set of double doors, while to the EAST and WEST are smaller doorways. The dark force sealing the NORTH doors has been dispelled, opening the way forward.\n"   
line5129c = "You approach the NORTH double doors. As you get closer you feel a dark energy pushing against you, preventing you from getting any closer. It would appear some dark force is sealing the doors shut. You'll need to find a way to dispel this force if you wish to proceed further into the palace...\n"
line5129d = "The dark force sealing the NORTH doors has been dispelled! Now the way NORTH through the double doors has been cleared\n"   
    #Palace 10
line5130 = "You enter a large dining hall in the middle of the palace. A long table stretches across the room, surrounded by high-backed chairs. The table is set with fine china and silverware, but it is covered in a thick layer of dust.\n"
line5131 = "Standing in the dining hall you begin to think about how long it's been since you've eaten. Unfortunately there doesn't appear to be any food left here; just dust and cobwebs. You notice a small unopened chest on the NORTH wall.\n"
line5131b = "Standing in the dining hall you begin to think about how long it's been since you've eaten. Unfortunately there doesn't appear to be any food left here; just dust and cobwebs. The chest in this room has already been opened and its contents safely in your possession.\n"
line5131c = "Standing in the dining hall you begin to think about how long it's been since you've eaten. Unfortunately there doesn't appear to be any food left here; just dust and cobwebs. You notice a small unopened chest on the NORTH wall. The wall to the EAST has opened up revealing a secret passage.\n"
line5131d = "Standing in the dining hall you begin to think about how long it's been since you've eaten. Unfortunately there doesn't appear to be any food left here; just dust and cobwebs. The chest in this room has already been opened and its contents safely in your possession. The wall to the EAST has opened up revealing a secret passage.\n"
line5132 = "You approach the chest on the NORTH wall. It's a small but sturdy iron chest. No chance of SMASHING this one. Do you want to try to OPEN it, or LEAVE it alone?\n"
line5132b = "You carefully attempt to open the chest, only to find it is locked tight. There's no way you'll be getting inside without the key...\n"
line5132c = "You decide to leave the chest alone for now and continue on your way.\n"
line5133d = "You use the DININGHALL KEY you found and successfully open the chest! Inside you find... a SKELETON KEY?.\n" #TODO PLACEHOLDER TEXT for loot
line5133e = "You attempt to SMASH the chest, but it is far too sturdy to break open. The recoil from your weapon bouncing off the chest causes you to fall on your butt. You knew this was coming but you did it anyway. Tsk.\n"
    #Palace 11
line5134 = "You enter another corridor. Strange sounds echo through the dark halls...\n"
line5135 = "The walls of the corridor are lined with more faded portraits and statues. You spot one particularly unusual statue of a large demon holding a large trident standing in a relief in the wall.\n"
line5135b = "The walls of the corridor are lined with more faded portraits and statues. The demon statue's remains have disappeared without a trace.\n"
line5136 = "You take a closer look at the demon statue. It has a strange life-like quality to it. As you study the statue more closely, you notice that the trident it holds appears to have three empty slots. Perhaps something fits into them?\n"
line5136b = "The slots look like they could fit a gemstone... Perhaps you can fit a gem you found earlier into one of these slots?\n"
line5136c = "You decide not to mess with the statue. Best to keep moving.\n"
line5136d = "You have no more gems to place into the trident's slots. Maybe you can find more elsewhere in the palace?\n"
line5137 = "You place the final gem into the trident's empty slot. The statue begins to rumble and shift. Suddenly the demon comes to life, letting out a deafening roar as it lunges at you with the trident!\n"
line5137b = "After a fierce battle you manage to defeat the Demon. As it falls to the ground, it crumbles into a pile of stone and dust, before vanishing completely. You take a moment to catch your breath before continuing on your way.\n"
line5137c = "You take a moment to reflect on the battle with the Demon. What an awful creature...\n"
    #Palace 12
line5138 = "You come to an intersection in the corridor. The room is cold and quiet. A single painting hangs at the end of the hall.\n"
line5138b = "You come to an intersection in the corridor. The room is cold and quiet. A lever has been revealed behind the painting.\n"
line5139 = "The room is like any other in the palace, filled with lavish decorations covered in dust and cobwebs. Still, something seems off about the painting at the end of the hall...\n"
line5139b = "The room is like any other in the palace, filled with lavish decorations covered in dust and cobwebs. The painting at the end of the hall has already been opened to reveal a hidden lever. Because what rich person's home wouldn't have secret switches and passages?\n"
line5140 = "You take a closer look at the painting. The painting was hung slightly crooked. Seeing the painting askew is pretty bothersome. You reach out to straighten it, but as you do, the painting swings open to reveal a lever! Neat.\n"
line5140b = "You examine the lever, wondering what'll happen when you pull it. Pull the lever? YES or NO?\n"
line5140c = "You pull back the lever. The palace shakes slightly as the sounds of rumbling can be heard coming from the EAST.\n"
line5140d = "You decide against pulling the lever. Probably best not to mess with anything else in this place. Right?\n"
    #Palace 13
line5141 = "You enter a grand library. Tall bookshelves line the walls forming rows, filled with dusty tomes and scrolls. A large wooden desk sits in the center of the room, covered in papers and quills.\n"
line5142 = "Looking around you think to yourself how many of these books must be filled with useless knowledge. Still, there might be something useful in here. You take a look at the desk and wonder if you should start your SEARCH there?\n"
line5142b = "Looking around you think to yourself how many of these books must be filled with incredible arcane knowledge. If only you had the time to read them all. Still, there might be something useful in here. You take a look at the desk and wonder if you should start your SEARCH there?\n"
line5143 = "You rummage through the papers and books on the desk. Most of it is just junk, but you do find a dusty old tome titled 'Secrets of the Night Creatures'.\n"    
line5143b = '"...Most already know that Werewolves turn in moonlight, but few know they are also attracted to it. You can often find them lurking around where the moon shines brightest..."'
line5143c = "...Vampires are said to be weak to sunlight and holy magic. They also have a strong aversion to garlic... But one of their greatest weaknesses (along with all undead) is silver weapons.\n" 
line5143d = "...Three precious gems were used to seal the demon in stone. It is said if all three are brought to it, the seal shall be broken and its power shall be released...\n" 
line5143e = "As you close the book, another piece of paper falls out from between the pages. A hastily scribbled message is written on it; you pick up the LIBRARY NOTE and read it:\n"
line5143f = '"The boy looks forward to his future, with ambition in his heart.\nThe soldier looks for glory on the battlefield, but only sees death.\nThe old man looks back on his youth, facing the setting sun.\nThe reaper looks on patiently, for none escape their fate."\n\nWhat a strange note... What could it mean? You take it and place it in your bag.\n"'
line5144 = "You search the shelves for more books, but all you find are titles such as 'How to Train Your Zombie: A Necromancers Guide', '101 Uses For Goblin Spleens', and 'The Lusty Bard of Harbor Town'... For such a nice place the owners taste in literature is quite questionable.\n" 
    #Palace 14
line5145 = "You enter a room filled with artworks, strange artifacts, and curiosities. Paintings, statues, and ancient looking relics line every wall and surface.\n"
line5146 = "You've never seen so much extravagant art in one place. It must all be worth a fortune. Too bad everything looks either too large, heavy, or fragile to take with you. At the very end of the room you spot a similar looking statue to the one you passed in the hall previously...\n"
line5146b = "You've never seen so much extravagant art in one place. It must all be worth a fortune. Too bad everything looks either too large, heavy, or fragile to take with you. The demon statue has disappeared revealing a hidden room behind it!\n"
line5147 = "You take a closer look at the statue. It appears to be a near replica of the demon statue you encountered earlier. Unlike the other statue this one isn't holding a trident; instead a deep emerald green gemstone is held in its hand.\n"
line5147b = "Underneath the demon statue is a small engraving that reads: 'Defeat my twin and we shall share our power.'\n"
line5147c = "It looks like the gemstone can be removed from the statue's hand. Do you want to take it? (YES or NO)\n"
line5147d = "You take the gemstone from the statue's hand and place the EMERALD GEMSTONE in your inventory.\n"
line5147e = "You decide against taking the gemstone. It looks valuable, but who knows what kind of curse it might have on it...\n"
line5147f = "You take a closer look at the statue. It appears to be a near replica of the demon statue you encountered earlier. The EMERALD GEMSTONE that was once held by the statue is now in your possession.\n"
line5147g = "It would seem defeating the Demon in the other room has caused the statue in this room to disappear as well. Now there is a hidden path behind it leading to another room NORTH.\n"
    #Palace 15
line5148 = "You enter a small chamber filled with strange symbols and markings on the walls. A large stone altar sits in the center of the room, covered in ancient runes and carvings.\n"
line5149 = "A faint glow emanates from the altar, illuminating the intricate designs etched into the stone. Upon the altar rests a magnificently crafted sword. You can feel a powerful energy radiating from it. \n"
line5149b = "The faint glow has disappeared from the altar now that SMELDAR\'s BANE is now in your possession; it's power now yours to wield.\n"
line5150 = "You approach the altar and take a closer look at the sword resting upon it. The blade is made of a shimmering metal that seems to glow with an inner light. The hilt is adorned with intricate designs and precious gems. This must be the legendary SMELDAR\'s BANE spoken of in ancient tales.\n\n You grab the blade and add it to your inventory.\n"
line5150b = "You approach the altar and take a closer look at the empty space where SMELDAR\'s BANE once rested. The evil warlock stands no chance against the blade's might! \n"
    #Palace 16
line5151 = "You enter a small room with nothing more than a single statue in the center. The statue depicts a young boy looking upward.\n"
line5152 = "The statue's expression is one of hopefulness and ambition. You can't help but wonder about the story behind this statue...\n\n It looks like there might be some way to rotate the statue?\n"
line5152b = "The statue's expression is one of hopefulness and ambition. You can't help but wonder about the story behind this statue...\n\n It doesn't look like it will rotate any further.\n"
line5153 = "You examine the statue more closely. It appears to be mounted on a circular base that allows it to be rotated.\n"
    #Palace 17
line5154 = "You enter a small room with nothing more than a single statue in the center. The statue depicts a cloaked figure holding a scythe.\n"   
line5155 = "The statue's expression is one of solemnity and inevitability. You can't help but wonder about the story behind this statue...\n\n It looks like there might be some way to rotate the statue?\n"
line5155b = "The statue's expression is one of solemnity and inevitability. You can't help but wonder about the story behind this statue...\n\n It doesn't look like it will rotate any further.\n"

    #Palace 18
line5156 = "You enter a small room with nothing more than a single statue in the center. The statue depicts a man with a wrinkled face and cane.\n"
line5157 = "The statue's expression is one of reflection and regret. You can't help but wonder about the story behind this statue...\n\n It looks like there might be some way to rotate the statue?\n"
line5157b = "The statue's expression is one of reflection and regret. You can't help but wonder about the story behind this statue...\n\n It doesn't look like it will rotate any further.\n"

    #Palace 19
line5158 = "You enter a small room with nothing more than a single statue in the center. The statue depicts a man in a full armor, holding a sword and shield.\n"
line5159 = "The statue's expression is one of valor and glory. You can't help but wonder about the story behind this statue...\n\n It looks like there might be some way to rotate the statue?\n"
line5159b = "The statue's expression is one of valor and glory. You can't help but wonder about the story behind this statue...\n\n It doesn't look like it will rotate any further.\n"
line5160 = "As you finish rotating the statue into its final position, you hear a faint click. Suddenly a magic sealing glyph shows itself on the ground beneath the statue. The glyph glows brightly for a brief moment before shattering, vanishing as quickly as it appeared. It appears you have broken some magical seal somewhere in the palace...\n"
line5161 = "You attempt to rotate the statue further, but it seems to be stuck in its current position.\n"

    #Lord's Chamber
line5162 = "You step into a grand chamber. The room is lavishly decorated with gold and jewels. A large throne sits at the far end of the room, flanked by two suits of armor. The Vampire Lord sits upon the throne, his eyes glowing with an otherworldly light.\n"
line5162b = "You step into a grand chamber. The room is lavishly decorated with gold and jewels. A large throne sits at the far end of the room, flanked by two suits of armor. The once powerful Vampire Lord is now nothing more than a pile of ash; another of SMELDAR's minions defeated.\n"
line5163 = "The Vampire Lord sits on his throne, seemingly unfazed by your presence. The air in the room is thick with tension as you prepare for the inevitable confrontation.\n"
line5163b = "With the Vampire Lord's defeat, the throne room feels noticeably lighter. The oppressive aura that once filled the space has lifted, and a sense of peace begins to settle in. Perhaps the Lord has something of value kept here...\n"
line5163c = "With the Vampire Lord's defeat, the throne room feels noticeably lighter. The oppressive aura that once filled the space has lifted, and a sense of peace begins to settle in. The room has been ransacked thoroughly; you're pretty confident you've grabbed everything of value in here.\n"
line5164 = 'You boldly announce your presence. The Vampire Lord rises from his throne, his eyes fixed on you. "So, you have made it this far, mortal. But your journey ends here. Prepare to meet your doom!"\n' #speak
line5164b = "Without hesitation you charge at the Vampire Lord, brandishing your weapon! The battle begins!\n" #attack
line5164c = 'You slowly approach the throne. The Vampire Lord rises from his throne, his eyes fixed on you. "So, you have made it this far, mortal. But your journey ends here. Prepare to meet your doom!"\n' #examine
line5164d = 'At last! The Vampire Lord has been vanquished! As he falls to the ground, his form dissipates into a cloud of ash. With his defeat, another of SMELDAR\'s minions has been defeated. From the pile of ash you grab the VAMPIRE\'S WARLOCK KEY! You take a moment to catch your breath after your well fought victory.\n'
line5165 = "You search the room for any valuable treasures. Hidden behind the throne, you find a small chest. Inside the chest, you discover a stash of gold coins and a mysterious gem with a blood red glow. You take the RUBY GEMSTONE and the coins and stash them away for safekeeping.\n"
line5165b = "You search the room again, but find nothing else of value. You've already grabbed everything worth taking here.\n"
line5166 = "You attempt to speak to the Vampire Lord, but he ignores your words, being a pile of ash and all now... "
line5166b = "You attempt to attack the Vampire Lord, but you just end up spreading his ashes around the room. Not very effective... and as if this place wasn't filthy enough.\n"

##52.SMELDARS TOWER*******************************

  #Tower 1 - Entrance
  #ambush
line5201 = "You approach the dark tower and gaze up the crooked spire. As you begin to step closer to the tower you hear a distant roar. Before you are able to take another step another roar shakes the earth around you. You manage to draw your weapon just a moment before a Dragon comes crashing into the Tower courtyard and attacks!\n"
line5202 = "Against all odds the Dragon is defeated! You stand victorious over the fallen beast, catching your breath as you prepare to enter the tower.\n"
  #intro
line5203 = "You approach the dark tower and gaze up the crooked spire. You sense your quest is drawing to a close.\n"
  #EXPLORE
line5204 = "Before you stands a massive stone door leading into the tower. The door has four keyholes, each one shaped differently. You'll need all four keys to unlock it presumably...\n\nSo far you've inserted 0 out of 4 keys.\n"
line5204b = "Before you stands a massive stone door leading into the tower. The door has four keyholes, each one shaped differently. You'll need all four keys to unlock it presumably...\n\nSo far you've inserted 1 out of 4 keys.\n"
line5204c = "Before you stands a massive stone door leading into the tower. The door has four keyholes, each one shaped differently. You'll need all four keys to unlock it presumably...\n\nSo far you've inserted 2 out of 4 keys.\n"
line5204d = "Before you stands a massive stone door leading into the tower. The door has four keyholes, each one shaped differently. You'll need all four keys to unlock it presumably...\n\nSo far you've inserted 3 out of 4 keys.\n"
line5204e = "The massive door leading into the tower is now open. The entrance looks like a dark void to another realm. A great evil awaits you inside...\n"
  #lock
line5204f = "The stone door blocking the entrance to the tower is sealed tight. You'll need all four keys to unlock it...\n"
 #EXAMINE
line5205 = "You examine the door more closely. There doesn't appear to be any way to open the door without the keys.\n"
line5205b = "The keyholes look like they could fit a warlock key you found earlier... Perhaps you can try putting one into the door?\n"
line5205c = "You decide not to touch the door. It's not like the you're in a rush to save the kingdom or anything.\n"
line5206d = "You have no more warlock keys to place into the keyholes. Maybe more are hidden among Smeldar's minions?\n"
line5206 = "You place the final warlock key into the keyhole. The door shifts and slides open, revealing a dark passageway beyond. A void like entrance greets you ominously.\n"
line5206b = "At long last, you have gained access to the tower. The final leg of your journey begins here...\n"

  #Tower 2
line5207 = "You enter the first chamber of Smeldar's Tower. You stand ready to face whatever challenges lie ahead.\n"
line5208 = "You stand in the dark chamber, your senses heightened as you prepare for whatever dangers may lurk within. You notice a skeleton chained to the wall...\n"
line5208b = "You stand in the dark chamber, your senses heightened as you prepare for whatever dangers may lurk within. The skeleton that was is now a pile of bones on the floor. Pretty disrespectful to just take his stuff and leave him like that but whats he gonna do about it?\n"
line5209 = "You approach the skeleton chained to the wall. It appears to be an adventurer who met a grim fate here. You notice it is clutching something in its left hand... If only there was some way to retrieve it. The skeleton's arm hangs just out of reach.\n"
line5209b = "You start swinging your weapon at the skeleton's arm, hoping to dislodge whatever it is holding. After the first strike the skeleton crumples into a bile of bones on the floor. You dig through the pile and find the item that was in the skeleton's bony clutches.\n\n It looks like it was holding an OBSIDIAN KEY wrapped in a note. You put both in your inventory and carry on.\n"
line5209c = "You jump up and try to grab the item in the skeleton's hand. Instead, you manage to grab the skeleton's arm and yank it to the ground. The skeleton crumples into a bile of bones on the floor. You dig through the pile and find the item that was in the skeleton's bony clutches.\n\n It looks like it was holding an OBSIDIAN KEY wrapped in a note. You put both in your inventory and carry on.\n\n"
line5209d = "You keep whacking at the skeleton's bones. It's not accomplishing much, but it's actually kinda fun desecrating a corpse.\n"
line5209e = "You continue to jump on the skeleton's bone pile. Maybe you should just stop. It's starting to get weird.\n"
line5209f = "You look at the pile of bones on the ground and think to yourself; 'Don't give up, skeleton.' \n"
  
  #Tower 3
line5210 = "You proceed through Smeldar's Tower. You take a moment to prepare yourself for the challenges ahead.\n"
line5211 = "The air in this room is magically charged, crackling with energy. You can feel the presence of powerful evil forces all around you.\n"
line5212 = "You cautiously examine the room. The walls are covered in strange runes and symbols that seem to pulse with dark energy. \n"
line5212b = "You recognize these symbols as runic traps designed to inflict harm on anyone passing into the next room. Would you like to try to disable them? (YES or NO)\n"
line5212c = "You successfully disable the traps! Now passage through this room should be safer.\n"
line5212d = "You decide against trying to disable the traps. Hopefully you can avoid them as you pass through...\n"
line5212e = "You manage to disable the traps, but not before triggering one! You take some damage from the magical blast.\n"
line5212f = "You take a look at the now defunct runes with a sense of accomplishment. Betcha feel pretty smart now, huh?\n"
line5212g = "You try exiting the room but are hit by a surge of dark magic!\n"
line5212h = "You carefully avoid the runic traps as you make your way through the room. That was a close one!\n"

  #Tower 4/7/8
line5213 = "You continue through Smeldar's Tower, every step leading you deeper into the heart of darkness.\n"
line5213b = "You move onward, your resolve strengthening with each passing moment.\n"
line5213c = "You press onward through Smeldar's Tower, determined to see your quest through to the end.\n"

line5214 = "You look around the room, but you cannot find the exit to the next room. The walls are bare stone, with no visible doors or passageways.\n"
line5214b = "The way to the next room has revealed itself, another of Smeldar's curses dispelled.\n"

line5215 = "You search the room for any means of opening up a hidden passageway or door, but turn up empty-handed. Perhaps the only thing left to try is to pick a direction and press on...\n"
line5215b = "The path forward has revealed itself. Time to move on...\n"

line5216 = "As you approach the wall a creature springs forth from it and attacks!\n"
line5216b = "The Wall Demon has been vanquished. You check the wall it emerged from and find it's just a wall.\n"
line5216c = "You cautiously approach the wall. As you touch it the illusion breaks and the way forward is revealed!\n"

  #Tower 5
line5217 = "You make your way deeper into Smeldar's Tower, taking caution as you navigate the treacherous corridors.\n"
line5218 = "The room is dark, and you can barely see your surroundings. You sense a malevolent presence lurking in the shadows.\n"
line5219 = "You search for the next stairwell, but find it is blocked by a heavy door. The only way through is to find a way to unlock it.\n"
line5219b = "The door blocking the stairwell has been unlocked. You can now proceed upward.\n"
line5219c = "Using your extraordinary thieving skills you could easily pick this lock in no time. Give it a shot? (YES or NO)\n"
line5219d = "With a few deft movements you manage to pick the lock on the door. The way to the stairwell is now clear.\n"
line5219e = "You decide against trying to pick the lock. Best not to risk it...\n"
line5219f = "You try to force the door open, but it is far too sturdy to budge.\n"
line5219g = "You might be able to use the SKELETON KEY in your inventory. Give it a shot? (YES or NO)\n"
line5219h = "You use the SKELETON KEY to unlock the door. How lucky is that? The way to the stairwell is now clear.\n"
line5219i = "You decide against using the SKELETON KEY right now. Better to wait until you're ready to proceed.\n"
line5219j = "You should be able to use the TOWER KEY in your inventory. Give it a shot? (YES or NO)\n"
line5219k = "You use the TOWER KEY to unlock the door. The way to the stairwell is now clear.\n"
line5219l = "You decide against using the TOWER KEY right now. Better to wait until you're ready to proceed.\n"
line5220 = "The key must certainly be nearby... try searching the room? (YES or NO)\n"
line5220b = "You manage to find the key! Now you can unlock the door.\n"
line5220c = "You search the room but come up empty-handed. Continue the search? (YES or NO)\n"
line5220d = "You decide to stop searching the room for now...\n"

  #Tower 6
line5221 = "You advance through the tower, ready to face whatever challenges lie ahead.\n"
line5222 = "Smeldar's minions seem to grow stronger with each passing floor. You can feel their malevolent presence closing in around you. As you look around the room you notice something strange about the wall to the NORTH...\n"
line5222b = "Smeldar's minions seem to grow stronger with each passing floor. You can feel their malevolent presence closing in around you. The wall to the NORTH has opened up revealing a hidden passageway!\n"
line5223 = "You approach the NORTH wall. Upon closer inspection you notice the stonework looks rough and uneven, as if it was hastily patched. You might be able to find a way through...\n"
line5223b = "You approach the NORTH wall. Upon closer inspection you notice the stonework looks rough and uneven, as if it was hastily patched. You bet you could SMASH right through that wall! Try breaking the wall? (YES or NO)\n"
line5223c = "You search the wall for any weak points or cracks. After a few moments of searching you throw caution to the wind and just start bashing the wall with all your might! A few moments later the stone wall gives way revealing a secret path ahead!\n"
line5223d = "You decide against trying to break through the wall. There's no time to mess around right now.\n"
line5223e = "That wall stood no chance against such a mighty hero such as yourself. May all walls tremble before your strength!\n"

  #Tower hidden room
line5224 = "You enter a hidden chamber within Smeldar's Tower. This small alcove seems to be untouched by Smeldar's darkness. A warm blue flame flickers in the center of the room, casting dancing shadows on the walls. Its warmth is inviting and calming. This seems like a safe place to REST and recover.\n"
line5225 = "You watch the blue flame flicker and dance. The warmth of the fire is soothing, and you feel a sense of peace wash over you. This seems like a safe place to REST and recover.\n"
line5225b = "The blue flame is nothing more than a few wispy embers now. Time to continue on your way.\n"
line5226 = "You take a moment to rest by the blue flame. The warmth of the fire soothes your weary body and mind. As you sit by the fire you feel your strength returning.\n"

 #Tower 9
line5227 = "You reach the upper levels of Smeldar's Tower. Before you are the doors to Smeldar's inner sanctum. The air grows thick with tension as you prepare for the final confrontation. There's no turning back once you continue.\n"
line5228 = "You stand before the grand doors leading to Smeldar's inner sanctum.  You can feel the weight of the moment pressing down on you as you prepare to face the dark warlock within. You should make sure you are completely prepared before the final fight.\n"

 #Tower 10 - Smeldar's Inner Sanctum
line5229 = "You take a deep breath and prepare to enter Smeldar's inner sanctum. The doors creak open slowly, revealing a dark chamber beyond. You step inside, ready to face the evil warlock.\n"
line5230 = '"So, you have finally arrived. I must admit I am impressed you made it this far. Defeating my four minions and besting my tower is no small feat. But your journey ends here. You will not stop me from reclaiming my rightful place as ruler of these lands!"\n'
line5231 = '"I offer you one last chance to spare yourself. Join me, hero. Lead my army to conquer these lands in my name and you may keep your life. Face me, and you will perish! The choice is yours, mortal."\n'
line5232 = 'You refuse the dark warlock\'s offer. You stand firm in your resolve to stop Smeldar and save the kingdom from his evil grasp. "Foolish mortal! I am the great Smeldar! None can stand up to my might! I shall crush you now, then the rest of the kingdom shall crumble!"\n'
line5233 = "You agree to join the dark warlock in his conquest of these once peaceful lands. You slaughter many innocent lives in the name of your dark lord Smeldar. As a reward for subjugating the kingdom and being Smeldar's most loyal servant, the warlock rips out your heart and throws off the top of the tower.  Now that the kingdom has fallen Smeldar will soon set his sights on the rest of the world...\n\n**********[Game Over: You have joined Smeldar's conquest!]**********\n" # bad ending
line5234 = 'Against all odds the evil warlock Smeldar falls in battle. "Curse you! Curse you ' #line part 1 add player name between lines
line5234b = '! This is not the end... I will return once more... and when I do, I will have my revenge!" Smeldaar shrieks with his last breath.\n' #line part 2 add player name between lines
line5235 = "With Smeldar's defeat, the tower around you begins to crumble and dissipate. Before long you find yourself standing alone in an empty clearing in the woods. No signs of Smeldar or his tower remain here. The sounds of life are already returning to the woods and the warmth of the sun finally reaches you. You make your way back to the Castle to claim your rewards and to be honored for your HEROIC deeds.\n"

line5236 = "**********[You have defeated Smeldar and saved the kingdom!]**********\n" # good ending
line5237 = "*****************[Results:]*****************"
line5238 = "**********[Thank you for playing!]**********\n"





